title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: low-fat split pea soup(serves 6)
directions: Cook peas until nearly tender, about 2 hours.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook until mushy and hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place 3 cans of whole corn, drained, into a 3 to 4-quart casserole baking pan.
Add beaten eggs and stir.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar and flour to corn and eggs, then cover corn with milk until milk has just covered the top of the corn.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes or until settled.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cream together next 2 ingredients. Mix next 3 ingredients; mix with creamed mixture.
Alternate last 3 ingredients with flour mixture.
Allow mixer to run 5 minutes. Alternate batter with apples in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start in cold oven.

title: pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg.
In a mixer bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds. Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy. Add egg, pumpkin and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
(Dough will be soft.)
Drop from a teaspoon 2-inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.
Makes about 48.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cut fruits and nuts; mix with part of flour.
Mix other ingredients.
Add fruits and nuts to cake mixture.
Bake in 275° oven 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Place pan of water under cake while baking.
(Grease pan and line with wax paper and then grease again.)

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir in Pet milk.
Boil to 236°, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage.
Remove.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Spread on cookie sheet, lined with waxed paper, to cool.

title: light fettucini alfredo
directions: Stir butter into cooked noodles.
Add Parmesan cheese, pepper, carrots and yogurt.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 12 x 14-inch pan. Cut squash fine and add to mixture. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ham oven sandwiches
directions: Divide 1 pound chipped ham over the buns and 1 thin slice of Swiss cheese.
Wrap in foil and heat in 400° oven for 15 minutes. Serves 12.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into pan; add eggs.
Cook slowly until slightly thick.
Pour over first 3 ingredients and stir well. Chill.
Pecans can be added.
Can be served individually on lettuce or in meringue cups topped with maraschino cherries.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter, then pour in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex and nuts; mix well.
Heat in oven 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Bake at 350°.
Or melt butter, then pour in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Place cereals, nuts and mixture in a Ziploc bag (shake well).
Transfer mixture to large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: grapefruit and orange cocktail salad
directions: Halve grapefruit and remove segments.
Save shells.
Cut orange into segments and combine with grapefruit segments.
Add sugar and rum.
Place mixture into clean grapefruit shells. Garnish with chopped mint and refrigerate until serving.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, zucchini and vanilla. Mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in nuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 96 cookies.
Store in airtight container.

title: hello dollies
directions: Crush graham crackers and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over graham crackers and pat down in pan.
Place chocolate chips over graham crackers.
Next, place butterscotch chips over chocolate chips, then place nuts and spread over pan.
Last, sprinkle coconut over all this mixture. Drizzle Eagle Brand milk over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take out.
Let cool and cut into bars.

title: jack's lamb stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper. Coat lamb evenly with flour mixture. Reserve leftover flour. Brown lamb well in hot butter in Dutch oven, along with quartered onion and garlic. Remove lamb when done. Add yellow onions, mushrooms and sugar to drippings in pan. Cook, covered, for 5 minutes or until browned.
Return lamb to Dutch oven. Add thyme, parsley and bay leaf. Toss with drippings to coat evenly.
Stir in 2 cups water and 1 cup wine. Place a large sheet of waxed paper over top of Dutch oven.
Place lid on top of paper, letting it hang over. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
(To keep from diluting sauce, pour off any liquid collecting on top of paper during cooking.)

title: country-style homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, light cream, salt and vanilla.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour ice cream mixture into 1 gallon canister of ice cream freezer.
Add peaches, strawberries or several mashed ripe bananas.
Add enough additional light cream to fill the canister 3/4 full or about 2 cups.
Freeze in freezer until firm.

title: walnut snacks
directions: Spread walnut halves
in shallow pan.
Dot with butter. Heat at 350° for
minutes.
Remove
from oven and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Remove from pan and cool on paper towel.

title: potato pudding
directions: Grate potatoes.
Mix with other ingredients except margarine. Melt margarine and add most to the other ingredients.
Save small amount and add to pan to keep from sticking.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: rainbow butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Mix well.
Divide dough in 3 parts and tint each part with a different color.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°. Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Take bones out.
Cook rice in broth.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Put in 2-quart dish and put corn flakes on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: parmesan olive potato topper
directions: Mix salad dressing, olives, red pepper, cheese, green onions and black pepper until well blended.
Serve over baked potatoes. Makes about 2 cups of topping.

title: nancy harmon's pork chop casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes and onions in 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dredge pork chops in 3 tablespoons flour.
Fry in oil.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon flour.
Stir until flour begins to brown.
Add milk and soup.
Pour over onions and potatoes.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chops are tender.
Serves 4.

title: hazelnusstorte(hazelnut cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 275° with rack in center of oven.
Beat egg yolks and the whole egg until thick and light.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar, then the 1 cup hazelnuts and bread crumbs.
Continue to beat until mixture forms a dense, moist mass.
Beat egg whites until very foamy, then add remaining 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; beat until whites form stiff peaks.
Mix about 1/4 of whites into hazelnut mixture.
Sprinkle with flour and gently fold in the remaining whites, just until no trace of whites remains Grease and flour 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all together, adding chips last.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in Bundt or tube pan.
Remove.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top while hot.

title: corn and shrimp
directions: In a skillet, combine soup, milk and paprika.
Stir over low heat until evenly pink.
Add the drained shrimp and corn.
Add pepper to taste.
Cover and cook through.
Serve over toast. Serves 4.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put in saucepan and heat the crushed pineapple, cherry or strawberry jello and sugar.
Stir until dissolved (do not add water).

title: taco casserole
directions: Add taco seasoning to ground beef. Mix together soups and taco sauce, then mix in with ground beef. Crush Tostitos and grate the cheese. Now layer chips, cheese and meat, ending with cheese. Put in oven until cheese melts at 375°.

title: peach schnapps fizzie's
directions: Mix all of the above in a blender and enjoy.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix spaghetti, hamburger, pizza sauce and cheese soup.
Put in a baking dish and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: marinated coleslaw(a make-ahead salad for quick meals)
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oil, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage, onion and pimentos.
Toss to mix well. Cover and chill at least 24 hours.
Salad keeps 3 to 4 weeks in the refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts or 12 to 16 servings.

title: golden egg corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Grease an 8-inch square baking dish or 10-inch skillet (iron). Stir together corn meal, flour and sugar. In a medium-size bowl, beat eggs with a fork just enough to blend yolks and whites. Stir milk and oil into eggs. Add dry ingredients and stir to blend thoroughly; beat just until smooth. Pour into greased pan and bake about 25 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Put flour, sugar and milk in a sealed quart jar.
Shake well. Pour over butter and peaches.
Bake at 350° until done.
Can use any fruit.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Do not stir.
Mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 3 tablespoons sugar. Pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fruitcake(sugar-free)
directions: Combine dry ingredients; blend in wet ingredients.
Divide batter between 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely.

title: cream cheesecake
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and margarine well and form into 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup crushed nuts on top. Beat eggs and almond. Add sugar and cream cheese. Fold in sour cream until blended well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (preheated for 10 minutes).

title: spicy pecans
directions: Put in 275° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes to distribute spices.
When done, drain on paper towel.
This is great for Christmas gifts.

title: lemon cordial
directions: Add sugar to glass or plastic bowl.
Put in lemon juice, grated rind of lemon, acids and epsom salts.
Pour on boiling water; stir to melt sugar.
Leave for 12 hours, then bottle, sealing bottles tightly.
Makes approximately 4 bottles.
To serve, add water for a refreshing drink.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 (9-inch) graham cracker pie crusts.
Sprinkle with vanilla wafer or graham cracker crumbs.
(No cooking.)
Keep refrigerated.

title: chewy cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar.
Mix well until dissolved.
Add flour, butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into shallow baking pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: tangerine and chicken salad
directions: Shred chicken into bite size pieces, then place them in a medium bowl along with tangerines, pecans, raisins and scallions.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Cream butter and peanut butters together.
Blend in sugar, vanilla and enough cream to make frosting spreadable.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Makes sufficient to cover top of a 9 x 13-inch cake or two dozen cupcakes.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk as directed on package, using large mixer bowl.
Add remaining milk and the pie filling mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold in coconut.
Spoon into crust. Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: lush cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts.
Pat like pie crust into 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over cooled crust.
Mix 2 packages instant chocolate pudding with 3 cups milk until thick.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with more Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: fruit or nut filled cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, flour, salt and sugar like pie dough.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix like pie dough.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add egg and vanilla mixture to flour and Crisco mixture.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll on powdered sugar.
Cut in small squares.
Put filling and pinch corners together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crock pot vegetable soup
directions: THIS NEEDS A 6 QUART OR LARGER CROCK POT.

title: bacon swiss bread
directions: Cut bread into 1 inch slices, leave attached at bottom. Combine butter, onions and mustard, spread on both sides of each slice. Cut each cheese slice diagonally into 4 pieces and place between slices of bread. Cut bacon in half width wise. Drape a piece over each bread slice.

title: judy's banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together.
Beat with mixer about 2 minutes.
Bake in two loaf pans at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: pickle mix
directions: Slice and layer first 5 vegetables.
Put sugar over top and let stand about 10 minutes.
Heat vinegar to a boiling point. Pour over the bowl of vegetables.
Cover.
Sit in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
This is a fresh and delightful pickle.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well, and pour into a 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for ten minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake until bubbly.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In skillet or Dutch oven, brown fryer pieces in hot oil. Remove chicken.
In same skillet, cook onions that have been sliced and minced garlic until tender, but not brown.
Return chicken to skillet.
Combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, oregano and bay leaves.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in white wine.
Cook chicken, uncovered, 15 minutes longer or until tender.
Remove bay leaves; skim off excess fat.
Serve over spaghetti or vermicelli.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry cream crunch
directions: Mix and press flour, pecans and margarine into a greased cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Take out of oven and let cool.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add soup and mix with hash browns, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Place in long baking dish and top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fried pie filling
directions: Cook fruit in separate containers until well done.
Add 1/4 cup white sugar to each container.
Mash with potato masher while hot.
Mix all together in one container.
Place in refrigerator. Let set overnight.
When ready to make pies, add to fruit mixture cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.

title: great american potato salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook onion, pepper, margarine, flour, milk and soup together until it thickens.
Put diced ham in casserole dish and sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Pour cooked mixture over ham.
Split biscuits in half and stretch as much as possible without tearing up.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. (I wait until it is about ready to take out of oven, then I sprinkle with cheese and let melt.)
A good way to use up leftover ham.

title: fall fruit saute
directions: Peel and slice the apples.
Halve the grapes.
Melt the butter in a frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add the apple, salt, pepper and dried tarragon, if using.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender, 3 or 4 minutes.
Stir in grapes and warm about 30 seconds.
Stir in fresh tarragon and lemon juice.
Serve.

title: savory beans and meatballs
directions: Blend beef, 1/4 cup onion, egg, salt, chili powder and pepper. Shape into 12 meatballs.
Cook in large skillet with remaining onion (1/2 cup).
Brown, and pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: company breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to crumble. Drain well.
Set aside.
Combine sausage and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together and cook over medium heat until desired thickness.

title: pink sauce with tortellini
directions: Cook tortellini as directed.
In saucepan, cook light cream, butter and grated cheese.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add crushed tomatoes.
Keep it on low.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Top tortellini with pink sauce.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and softened butter.
Beat with mixer until blended.
Sift together 1 1/3 cups flour, 2 teaspoons of baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Stir sifted ingredients into the peanut butter mixture.
Spread into lightly greased pan.
Spread over the top 1/4 cup chopped salted peanuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange-ginger frosty
directions: Place 4 tall glasses in freezing compartment of refrigerator. Mix orange juice and ginger ale.
Fill frosted glasses with cracked ice.
Pour mixture over it.
Garnish with 1 lemon slice and 1 thin orange slice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Prepare ingredients as listed.
Mix everything in a very big bowl.
Use broth from turkey to keep dressing moist.
Spoon into a greased baking dish or stuff into turkey in the last 30 minutes of turkey baking.

title: spaghetti squash(zucca di spaghetti)
directions: Halve squash and scoop out seeds.
Place cut side down, in
a glass
baking
dish with 1 cup water.
Cover with clear plastic wrap.
Place
in microwave and cook on High for 10 to 15 minutes until tender.
When tender, with fork scrape squash out
of
shell forming thin spaghetti.
In large skillet saute onion in butter until onion is translucent.
Add squash, salt and pepper and
cook for about 15 to 20 minutes on medium-low heat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Take off heat and let cool.
Add marshmallows, cottage cheese and pecans.
Last, fold in whipped cream.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of this for top crust.
Pat remaining crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top that layer with peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Spread evenly.
Crumble remaining mixture over that.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Pour milk over cracker meal and let stand until dissolved. Season meat with salt, pepper, Accent and onion.
Beat eggs and add to milk mixture.
Pour all into meat and roll into small balls.
Brown meat well on all sides.
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream, water and mushrooms.
Pour over browned balls (in large casserole or roaster).
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
(If gravy is a little thick, you may add more milk before serving.) Serves 25 people.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut tomatoes, lettuce and onions as you would for salad.
Add kidney beans (drained).
Add sharp cheese and toss.

title: delicious butterscotch bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar, beaten egg, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix.
Add nuts.
Put into a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Recipe can be doubled.
When cool, frost.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Have
butter
and
eggs
at
room
temperature.
Cream butter, shortening	and
sugar
good.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and baking powder together, then add milk and flour to mixture.
Place
in a greased and lightly floured tube pan. Place in a
cold	oven
and
bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: mud pie
directions: Put it in a pan that is teeny-tiny.
You sit in the sun and when it is hot, I think it will turn into a pie.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and spread in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish or 12 x 12 x 2-inch.
Cover chicken with drained water chestnuts.

title: pineapple cherry dump cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour in pineapple.
Spread out.
Pour or spoon on cherry pie filling. Level out.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix.
Flatten.
Sprinkle on nuts. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rosie's pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter well.
Add flour and eggs alternately and gradually.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix taco seasoning, sour cream and mayonnaise and chill overnight for 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: butterscotch goodies
directions: Grease Bundt or similar cake pan well. Put in frozen rolls. Sprinkle dry pudding mix over top of rolls.
Cover with cinnamon and nuts.
Mix brown sugar and oleo and bring to boil.
Cool. Spread over rolls.
Cover and let stand overnight at room temperature.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
The gooey stuff settles down through rolls as they rise.

title: bacon wrapped breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut bacon slices in half. Wrap each breadstick with 1 slice of bacon. Line cookie sheet with wax paper. Bake 15 minutes or until bacon is brown. While warm, roll in Parmesan and garlic powder mixture.

title: cheese ball(appetizer)
directions: Soften cheese.
Add pineapple, pepper, onion, salt and 1 cup pecans; mix well.
Divide into 2 portions.
Make 2 balls; roll in remaining pecans.
Makes 2 balls.

title: horseradish dipping sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and blend well.
Place in a covered container and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon. Pare and core cut apples into eights. Place in deep baking dish. Add sugar mixture, lemon rind, lemon juice and water. Dot with butter.
Cover with pie crust. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until apples are tender.

title: mother's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease and flour an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Beat together the butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add the eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in the chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add the dry ingredients to the butter and egg mixture, alternating with sour cream, pudding mix and butter mixture.
Stir in the milk to thin the batter.
Pour batter in pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Fill or frost as desired.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In large frying pan over medium heat, saute chopped onion in oil until soft.
In small bowl, combine ketchup, sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and black pepper; add to pan with onion.
Add chicken to pan.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 25 to 35 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken to serving platter. Dissolve cornstarch with 2 tablespoons of water; add to pan with sauce.
Bring sauce to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken before serving.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/3 cup tomato sauce with all remaining ingredients.
Put in un-greased loaf pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In Dutch oven, saute garlic, onions and green pepper in oil. Add okra, tomatoes, water and salt;
boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp to Dutch oven; stir.
Return to a boil, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add crabmeat, oysters and parsley to shrimp mixture.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Ladle gumbo into 8 individual bowls, stir gently to mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: raspberry parfaits
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Measure 3/4 cup gelatin; spoon in sherbet and stir until melted.
Chill until set.
Add cold water and ice cubes to remaining gelatin and stir constantly until gelatin starts to thicken, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove any unmelted cubes.
Fold in fruit and spoon into 6 parfait glasses. Chill until set.
Spoon sherbet mixture into glasses.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "4" layer dessert
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: holiday ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar together and then stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients except preserves and Cool Whip. Pour into an
x
x
2-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes. Cool completely.
Split
to make two layers.
Spread preserves and Cool Whip on bottom layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top layer.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat peanut butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy. Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup Nestle Toll House chips. Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Immediately sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes, until chips become shiny and soft.
Spread them evenly over top.
Completely cool before cutting into bars.

title: rigatoni i
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground meat. Add garlic powder, salt and pepper. Drain off grease. Add 1 jar of spaghetti sauce and simmer. Boil rigatoni as directed on package and drain. Add some butter according to taste and garlic powder. Mix. Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour the other jar of spaghetti sauce over noodles. Add meat mixture. Mix in Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and mix well. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chocolate drink
directions: Mix well in large container.
Use 1 tablespoon for 1 cup of hot chocolate mix.
Just add hot water and stir.

title: chicken noodle or rice soup
directions: Clean and wash chicken parts in a cooking pot.
Add the chicken parts to the 1 1/2 gallons of water and let cook until the meat
comes
from the bone.
Remove the meat and any bones that are
left
in
the water.
Remove the meat from the bones and let cool.
Add
the
chopped
onions, celery, salt, pepper and 1/2 pound noodles or 1/2 pound of rice, whichever soup you desired.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.
Store leftover pie in the refrigerator.

title: microwave eggless cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil and milk.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in 9-inch square or pie pan in microwave for 9 minutes.
No need to cover.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and oleo.
Shape into balls.
Cool 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate.
Dip the balls into the chocolate with a toothpick.
Cool.
Makes about 100.

title: gwen's chili sauce
directions: Cook the vegetables until celery is soft.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer; cook until it thickens, stirring frequently.
Seal in scalded jars.
(I usually double this recipe!)

title: pork chops with white wine and shallots
directions: Heat oil or butter in heavy 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Arrange chops in pan without sides touching and saute on all sides until rich golden color, turning once; use wooden spoons or spatulas to turn so meat is not pierced.

Reduce heat to low; if using electric range, remove pan from direct heat until burner cools down and continue cooking chops, turning once, until they are semi-firm when pressed with finger, about 10 minutes per side; do not overcook.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper. Transfer chops to ovenproof platter; tent with foil and set in 350° oven.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of fat from skillet. Place skillet over high heat.
Add 1/2 cup minced shallot and saute until softened, about 1 minute.
Stir in white wine and chicken stock.
Boil over high heat, stirring constantly and scraping up any browned bits clinging to bottom of pan, until reduced by 1/2.
Pour wine sauce over chops.
Sprinkle with either minced fresh chives or green onion tops.

title: cleaning solution
directions: Put all in gallon jug.
Fill with water.
Pour into spray bottle and use as you would 409.

title: alum pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers 4 days in strong salt.
Wash and rinse 3 or 4 times.
Slice and soak in 1 small box alum, dissolved in 1 gallon of water.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let soak 2 days.
Pour alum water off.
Wash good.
Pour 1 gallon of vinegar on cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
Drain vinegar off.
Put a layer of cucumbers and a layer of sugar and pickling spice.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Add butter to sugar and beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add wafers (crushed) alternately with milk.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick baked apples
directions: Cut apples vertically into halves. Remove cores.
Place halves, cut side up, in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Mix brown sugar and flour.
Spoon into center of each half.
Place 1/2 teaspoon margarine on brown sugar mixture on each half.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High until apples are tender (3 to 4 minutes).

title: auntie's barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into large meatballs.
Place 1 layer deep in flat pan.

title: *meatballs with onions casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and form into egg size meatballs.
Roll in flour. May be fried or placed in casserole without frying.

title: tuna rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package. Cool.
Toss rice, tuna, green beans, tomatoes, scallions, olives and 1/2 cup of the dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine cheese, flour, milk, butter and parsley in 1-quart saucepan. Cook on low until cheese is melted. Stir often.
Boil sliced potatoes 8 minutes.
Put ham in large baking dish.
Add potatoes.
Pour cheese mixture over ham and potatoes.
Mix well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, with lid for 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, lemon juice, margarine and salt in saucepan. Heat mixture, stirring occasionally, until it boils.
Use for basting.
Grill chicken breasts over medium hot coals for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Baste frequently and turn chicken every 2 to 3 minutes while grilling.
Sprinkle generously with Cajun seasoning for the last 2 minutes of cooking.
Excellent served with broccoli and baked potatoes.

title: nachos
directions: Lay Doritos/tortillas on ovenproof dish or cookie sheet; grate cheese on top of chips.
Place chilies on each chip.
Bake in a 400° oven until cheese melts.
Refried beans or taco meat may be added, if desired.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Mix tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce; simmer 5 minutes.
Put meat in 9 x 13-inch dish; spread 1 cup of sour cream on top.
Sprinkle 3 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Unroll crescent rolls and spread on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on rolls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pryor high school peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Spray sheet with Pam.
Roll dough into balls with wet hands.
Flatten cookies with tines of a fork to crisscross tops.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes for crisp cookies or at 350° for 10 minutes for soft cookies.

title: janet's sugar cookies
directions: Soften butter to room temperature by setting it out (do not microwave) because it will not soften, just melt.
Mix in the eggs and sugar and beat well.
Add salt, baking powder and baking soda; beat well again.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour and mix it all in until an uniform dough is made.
Chill dough in the refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Cover with wrap to keep moist. Roll out about 1/4-inch.
Bake in oven at 350° to 375° until brown on bottom.
Use cookie cutters; brush with beaten egg whites and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine water, sugar, salt and butter, yeast, egg and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat with mixer until blended.
Stir in 2 to 3 more cups of flour, enough to make stiff dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double.
Push down and divide into rolls.
Place in greased pan and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes and place in saucepan with half of the butter.
Heat over medium heat until melted.
Place vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture in and mix well. Melt remaining butter and stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle mixture over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: volcanic shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender. Blend on low, then high until frothy.
Poor into glass. Drink and enjoy!

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl. Mix well. Freeze into molds (3-ounce paper cups work well). Insert a wooden stick when partially frozen.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Place croutons in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Brown sausage; cool. Place sausage and cheese on top of croutons.
Beat eggs, mustard and 2 cups milk together.
Pour over meat and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with cut vegetables such as: carrots, green peppers, celery, radishes, cucumbers, mushrooms and/or cauliflower.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix jello pudding and Dream Whip pudding mix with milk.
Layer bananas and vanilla wafers in a pan or glass bowl.
Spread mix on 1 layer at a time until all ingredients are finished.
Put Cool Whip on top (optional).

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter.
Add flour, salt and mustard; blend.
Then add milk, pepper and salt.
In 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of carrots, cheese and bread crumbs.
Pour sauce over this mixture and bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: wild rice salad
directions: In a small saucepan, bring the currants and sherry to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Place the wild rice, 2 cups of boiling stock and 2 tablespoons butter in the top of a double boiler over simmering water.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, place the brown rice, the remaining 2 2/3 cups boiling stock and 2 tablespoons of butter in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook until all the water is absorbed, about 50 minutes.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; mix well.
Spread 1/3 of meat sauce in 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange 1/2 of the uncooked noodles over sauce.
Spread with 1/2 of the Ricotta.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Double wrap tightly with Saran Wrap.
Cook on High for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Cook on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a greased sheet pan or 1 hour in a Bundt pan.

title: crazy chocolate dump cake
directions: Put ingredients into a mixing bowl in the order listed.
Do not stir until water is added last.
Beat all together for 3 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for approximately 25 minutes at 325°.

title: oven spanish rice
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in shortening or salad oil until tender, but not brown; stir in spaghetti sauce mix, tomatoes, uncooked rice, salt and water.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Sprinkle with shredded sharp cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mints
directions: Mix together all ingredients thoroughly.
Be sure it is of right consistency.
Press in mint molds.
Turn out onto waxed paper to dry.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator or freezer.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Layer: crushed Doritos, chicken, onions, soups, Ro-Tel, broth and a few more chips. Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Lay slices of Velveeta on top; put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook in oil, uncovered, 10 minutes per side, turning once.
Cook over medium heat.
Add broth, juice and basil.
Cook 10 minutes longer over low heat or until tender; covered.
Marinate in covered bowl in refrigerator 4 to 24 hours.
Serve thinly sliced, hot or cold.

title: oven-baked caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, syrup, margarine, and salt for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir and pour immediately over popcorn.
Mix well.
Put into large roaster and bake for 45 minutes at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes while in oven and several times during cooking period.

title: vodka slush
directions: Bring to a boil and then cool.
Steep 4 green tea bags in cups of boiling water and cool.
Mix water/sugar, green tea, 12 oz. can lemonade, 12 oz. can orange juice and 1 pint vodka in a 5 quart ice cream bucket and freeze. Stir once in a while. Serve 1/2 slush with 1/2 7-up.

title: sour cream blueberry pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat 5 minutes with electric mixer or until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour filling in pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Mix 3 tablespoons flour, 3 tablespoons butter (softened) and 3 tablespoons chopped pecans or walnuts, stirring well.
Sprinkle on top of pie and bake 10 more minutes.
When pie has baked 5 minutes, spread topping with fork evenly over entire pie.
Chill before serving.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, Crisco and salt in a large bowl. Add water and vanilla. Beat well, then add mayonnaise. Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes. Cool before frosting.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with sugar and water; pour in punch bowl.
Add ice cream.
Pour 7-Up and ginger ale over and serve.

title: basic sweet roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine margarine, sugar and milk and warm until sugar dissolves and margarine melts.
Cool to lukewarm. Add eggs.
Mix in flour.
Stir in flour, then dump onto well floured board and knead in enough flour that it isn't sticky, but is soft.
Cover; set in a warm place and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down and form into any type of dinner or sweet roll.
Bake rolls at 425° approximately 20 minutes.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Lightly brown the hamburg with minced onion.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam.
Layer in this order: potatoes, peas, carrots and hamburg.
Mix the vegetable juices with 1 can of tomato soup and pour over the top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° (covered) for 2 hours.
Take cover off for the last 15 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve and cool first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: fresh apple cake(yields 16 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt or tube cake pan.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In large mixer bowl, combine cooking oil and sugar; cream thoroughly and add eggs and vanilla.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and apples and beat on slow speed just until thoroughly blended.
Pour into tube pan and bake one hour and fifteen minutes.
Contains approximately 285 calories per serving.

title: turkey mushroom bake
directions: Rinse wings; place in pot of water and bring to a boil. Simmer for 1 1/2
to
2 hours.
Remove skin and debone turkey.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Melt butter, whisk in eggs, sour cream, muffin mix; add corn with remaining liquid; mix well. Pour into 2 qt. greased casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise for potato salad
directions: Blend dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and blend with vinegar and water.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Heat until it thickens.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and cover.
Let set 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Add oat mixture; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to mixture.
Pour in well-greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Let cool (do not drain).
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add walnuts and cooled raisins.
Drop on baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: old fashioned lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Add boiling water slowly.
Cook over water 30 minutes.
(Cook this long or it will be runny.)
Mix grated lemon rind and juice with egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Add to mixture in double boiler.
Cook 2 minutes. Remove and add butter.
Top with meringue and bake until meringue is brown.

title: tangy fruit gelatin
directions: In small saucepan, heat water to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour 2 1/4 cups hot gelatin mixture into blender container.
Set remaining 1 1/4 cups gelatin mixture aside.
Add yogurt, cream cheese and lemonade concentrate to gelatin mixture in blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into 10-inch glass pie plate or quiche pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Arrange fruit over top.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, honey and salt in large bowl.
Stir until blended.
Add butter and water.
Beat 2 minutes, then add 1 1/2 cups more flour; beat until thick and elastic.
Stir in whole wheat flour.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make soft dough.

title: caramel cake icing
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar; cook over low heat for 2 minutes. Stir constantly.
Add milk and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool and add confectioners sugar until right consistency to spread.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat, add cocoa and stir until well blended.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts.
Spread in pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: If using whole kernel corn, drain it.
If using cream-style corn, use as is.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange icing
directions: Blend ingredients. Ice cookies.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar adding eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and milk; beat until very creamy.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oblong pan at 450° until done.

title: cinnamon pie
directions: Beat all ingredients in a bowl. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in brown grocery bag.
In microwavable bowl put butter, brown sugar, salt, baking soda and corn syrup. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Pour in brown bag over corn.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Roll up sack and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: bobby palmer's christening cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes.
While cake is baking, melt caramels and butter. Add milk.
Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pour this mixture on top of cake that has baked.
Pour remaining batter on top of caramel mixture.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over this and bake for an additional 15 to 25 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oblong casserole dish.
Make batter by mixing together the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour this batter over melted margarine.
Top with peaches that have been sweetened and almond extract has been added to.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. The batter will rise to the top and peaches will go to the bottom.

title: butter baked carrot sticks
directions: Pare carrots; cut in 3-inch long sticks.
Place in shallow 6-cup baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Dot with butter. Cover.
Bake at 400 ° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: In saucepan, heat 1/2 cup chocolate chips and margarine over low heat until melted. Cool.

title: mulled apple cider
directions: Simmer several hours with a cinnamon stick. Make in multiples for large groups.

title: elegant steak
directions: Brown meat in 1 1/2 tablespoons oil.
Add onions and mushrooms. Cook briefly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in ginger, soy sauce, soup, sherry and garlic salt.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.
Also good with pork.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Beat eggs and almond extract with fork, add cherry pie filling.
Mix with wooden spoon into cake mix.
Add no other liquids or ingredients.
Bake in floured and greased 13 x 8 1/2-inch cake pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry pineapple salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add pie filling and drained pineapple. Let set in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt sugar and butter in an iron skillet.
Cool.
Add well beaten eggs to sugar mixture, then beat in flour and baking powder.
Add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased shallow pan and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Put margarine and Crisco on large bowl and allow to soften at room temperature.
Add sugar and cream, using electric mixer.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating continuously.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into a separate bowl.
Gradually add flour mixture to other mixture, alternately with milk.
Continue beating.
Then add vanilla and lemon flavoring, crushed pineapple and juice. Pour into greased and floured steeple pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter milk shake
directions: Put peanut butter, milk and sugar into blender.
Mix for 2 to 3 minutes.
If desired, may put more of any/either ingredient.

title: quick brown bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients in a bowl; mix in bread crumbs.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in raisins.
Mix together the eggs, buttermilk and molasses; stir into flour mixture until blended. Pour batter into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or three 10 x 5 x 3-inch bread pans.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes for oblong or bread pans.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Place about 9 large chocolate peppermint patties on cake immediately after removing from the oven.
As they melt, spread the chocolate and fondant to cover the top of the cake.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Salt and pepper tomato slices; dip in cornmeal.
Heat about 1/2 cup shortening in skillet on top of stove until hot.
Cook until golden brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat eggs; stir in corn meal, sugar, cream and vanilla. Pour into
an unbaked pie shell and bake for 35 or 40 minutes at

title: green salad
directions: Fix early in the morning; put in refrigerator and chill.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Combine macaroni, sauce and fruit and let stand overnight. (Mix well.)
Next day, add 1 large container Cool Whip and mix well.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage in frypan. Drain on paper towel.
Be sure it is all broken and mixed up while frying. Potato masher works well.
Layer croutons in bottom of greased pan.
Then cheese, then mushrooms and then the sausage.
In a blender mix milk, eggs, mushroom soup and dry mustard, pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
If made the night before, allow 2 hours.

title: ida's shrimp mold
directions: Heat tomato soup as is and add softened cream cheese.
Blend until melted, then add mayonnaise.
Mix the 2 packets of Knox gelatine with 1/2 cup cold water.
Add this to the tomato soup mixture; stir until well mixed.
Add celery and onions, mixing them gently.
Add shrimp.
Grease mold with mayonnaise.
Pour mixture into the mold and refrigerate to set.
Serve with crackers.

title: best ever enchilada torte
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain well.
Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Simmer for 15 minutes on low.
Mix taco sauce and tomato sauce in bowl.
Spread 1/3 of sauce mixture in 9 x 13 pan.

title: cheese-meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, soup and crackers well.
Place half of mixture in loaf pan.
Place cheese.
Add remaining mixture.
Lay strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grape-nuts custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Warm milk and pour over Grape-Nuts. Let stand 15 minutes.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and cinnamon, stirring until well mixed.
Pour into a deep 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan and spread a little tomato juice or catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Stir together dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture; mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook hamburger; drain, rinse and drain again.
Add water and rest of ingredients, except macaroni.
Simmer until potatoes and carrots are tender, but firm.
Add macaroni and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: italian rice salad
directions: Blend dressing and mayonnaise.
Stir in vegetables.
Add rice and toss well.
Chill and serve.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until tender.
Cool.
Cut into pieces. Mix remaining ingredients.
Place potatoes in a baking dish.
Pour mixture over potatoes and mix gently.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cheesy tuna melt
directions: Heat broiler.
Mix tuna, onion, pickle and pepper.
Mix Cheez Whiz, salad dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Add tuna mixture; mix lightly.
For each sandwich, spoon tuna mixture onto bottom halves of buns; top with tomato.
Broil for 2 to 3 minutes or until Cheez Whiz begins to melt.
Serve with top halves of buns.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
3 minutes.

title: tex-mex chicken fiesta
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together soup, chili powder, cumin and water.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add all the remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup each cheese.
Spoon mixture into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Or cover; refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Top with sour cream, salsa and cilantro, if desired.
Prep time: 20 minutes.
Cooking time: 20 minutes plus standing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake into 1-inch slices.
Arrange cake slices in a single layer of an ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding mix for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Beat in ice cream.
Pour over cake and chill.
In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries.
Chill until partially set.
Spoon over pudding mix.
Chill until firm. Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: apple bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add oil and beat until creamy.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Gradually blend into egg mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in 12 x 17-inch ungreased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While cake is still warm, top with frosting.

title: krispies scotcheroos
directions: In large saucepan cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Press in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips until smooth and spread over cereal mixture.
Chill.
(Can use chocolate chips only, just use 2 cups.)

title: 7 minute chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, thawed vegetables, soup and milk.
Add 1 cup French fried onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with remaining onions.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Prepare celery.
In mixing bowl, blend cheeses, cream and nuts.
Stuff celery, chill, then serve.

title: mocha creme liqueur
directions: In saucepan combine sweetened condensed milk, light cream and instant coffee.
Cook and stir over medium heat until coffee crystals are dissolved.
Gradually stir about half of the hot mixture into the egg yolk.
Return all of it to saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir the mixture over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove the saucepan from the heat.
Stir in whiskey, Kahlua and chocolate.
Cool mixture.
Bottle and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 1/4 cups.
Keeps up to 2 months.

title: top bananas
directions: Add ingredients together and dig in!

title: crunchy snacks
directions: Layer a single layer of saltines in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil together margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over crackers and bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Place on oven door and spread chocolate chips; stir slightly until melted.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter (I use Skippy super crunchy) and butter.
Make into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Melt chocolate bar and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and put on wax paper until set.
Makes 3 pounds of candy for about $3.00.

title: my mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Mix.
Sift flour and other dry spices. Add to first mixture. Then add oatmeal, wheat germ and raisins. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
(I make each cookie more than 1 teaspoon.)
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until they look and feel cooked enough. Don't dry out.

title: whatzit pie
directions: Blend and mix well all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes between 300° and 350°.

title: banana shake
directions: Peel ripe banana; cut in half and freeze.
Cut the banana into 3 or 4 pieces.
Put the ice cubes in blender on lowest speed to chop up the ice.
Add the pieces of frozen banana and allow them to be chopped up.
Add the milk, flavoring and sugar substitute and blend for a few seconds to mix.
Pour in a glass and serve.

title: stromboli
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Divide bread dough into two halves. Roll each half out to form a rectangle.
Mix first 7 ingredients together and spread evenly over the dough.
then layer the onion, pepperoni and mushrooms, or any other ingredients that you like. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Fold dough over and pinch together. Then brush with egg whites.
Bake for 30-40 minutes.

title: mile high dessert
directions: Combine and press graham cracker mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place strawberries, sugar, lemon juice, salt and egg whites in a large mixing bowl.
Mix at high speed for 15 minutes. Beat whipping cream until fluffy and gently add to strawberry mixture. Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla. Combine strawberry and whipping cream mixture.
Spread on top of graham cracker crust. Freeze.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Add flour and seasonings and mix well.
Pinch off small amount; work into thin circle and press around olive.
Bake on greased sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Melt all in double boiler over hot water.
Add 1 box of powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Frost immediately.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and applesauce. Add zucchini and mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: italian fiesta vegetables
directions: In a large skillet or wok, melt butter over high heat. Add olive oil and garlic; stir for 1 minute.
Add onion and stir 3 minutes. Add broccoli and red pepper; cook for 4 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley, thyme, salt and pepper.
Stir and serve at once. Serves 4 or 5.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Bring to boil 1 cup of water, margarine and onions; add broccoli and cook until thawed.
When this comes to a boil, remove from heat and add 1 cup Minute rice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in jar of cheese and cream of celery soup.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
With a pastry blender, cut the shortening into the flour until it resembles coarse crumbs.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour together in top of double boiler.
Mix milk and beaten egg and add to dry ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add pineapple and pour into baked pie shell.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Chop tomatoes in colander.
Pour boiling water; let drain. Food process apples on chop after peeled and cored.
Cook 1 hour in enameled pan.
Then hot seal in jars; 1 quart makes one 8-inch pie.
Can also be used in cookies and fruit cake.
A 70 year old goodie.

title: crunchy buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Shape into small balls.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Dip each ball with toothpick into chocolate that has been
melted with Crisco.
Roll in crushed walnuts.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve jello in juices from cherries and pineapple, heated. Add colas, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Grate frozen cheese over top (gives appearance of snow).
Refrigerate and congeal.
Serves 10.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Serve with crackers, chips or celery.

title: fruit cup
directions: Combine three or more fruits that look and taste well together.
Usually have one very colorful fruit and one outstanding flavor.
Don't let them fight.

title: strawberry and fig jelly
directions: Put all ingredients into a pan and bring to boil. Cook for 4 minutes. Put in small canning jars. Great gift to give at the holidays. Good on toast, biscuits or with cream cheese.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: turkey-rice casserole
directions: Mix soup with 1 can water.
Stir in next 4 ingredients and put in buttered 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350°
about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: yellow punch for all
directions: Mix lemonade powder with water.
Add orange juice and pineapple juice.
Chill well.
Just before serving, add Sprite. May be garnished with dips of sherbet or an ice ring.
Serves over 100.

title: chicken paprika with sour cream
directions: Saute the onion until translucent.
Mix in paprika.
Add chicken.
Cover and let it cook slowly.
A spoonful of water can be added to prevent burning.
When chicken is done, add salt and 1/2 pint of sour cream.
Do not let sour cream boil.
Serve over boiled noodles.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Sift together and mix thoroughly in a large bowl the first 6 ingredients.
Combine and stir into dry ingredients the rest of the ingredients only until the mixture is well moistened.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool before cutting.
This is one of my family's favorites!
I have to double the recipe if I get any!

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and garlic in blender. Add oil very slowly, with blender at slow speed.
Add poppy seed. To get a thick dressing that will not separate easily, take your time and add the oil very slowly.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put chicken in pan.
Pour sweet and sour dressing over chicken and mix water in bottom of pan with dressing.
Then sprinkle Mrs. Dash on top of chicken and cook for hour or until done.

title: ravioli
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Make a well in the center and place eggs and water in well.
Blend by hand until a ball forms. If too dry, add more water.
Place on floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover with bowl and let rest 20 minutes.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt oleo, mix in crumbs, pecans, coconut, sugar and vanilla. Add peanut butter, mixing well.
Roll in walnut size balls, place on wax paper; melt chocolate bits and paraffin over hot water. Dip balls in mixture and place back on wax paper.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls
into
jello
roll	pan.
Bake for 10 to 13 minutes at	325°.
Spread
cream cheese mixture over dough and sprinkle veggies and cheese on top.
Cut into squares.

title: lime jello dump salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice to boiling.
Remove from heat. Stir in Jell-O.
Let set until thick as egg whites.
Blend the cream cheese well.
Fold
into
whipped cream.
Fold this into Jell-O. Pour into a cold
dish.
I
also like to add 1 cup of white grapes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add flour until you're able to drop the dough so it makes a drop cookie.
Grease cookie sheet and preheat oven to 400°.
Let cookies cook for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine tomato sauce, water, onions, green peppers, salt, sugar, mustard and pepper in saucepan.
Cover and bring to full boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes, covered.
Stir with fork.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely before icing.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer pineapple, cherries, cake mix, oleo and pecans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° to 425° until top is brown.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, tossing to mix well.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almond extract, in 2-quart microproof bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook 13 minutes or until berries pop.
Stir in almond extract.
Let stand until cool. Cover and refrigerate.

title: salad pizza
directions: Unroll crescent wedges and place in pizza pan.
Shape.
Bake crust at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool at least 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over crust.
Add any vegetables you wish: celery, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, peppers, etc. Better to chill an hour before eating.

title: simple chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients. Bring to boil.
Simmer 30 to 60 minutes or more.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and fold in 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Season to taste.
Butter buns and fill with mixture.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Place in oven at 250° for 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: rice chex snacks
directions: Melt chips and margarine.
Mix in peanut butter.
Add mixture to Chex cereal (in a large bowl).
Toss until well coated.
Put in a large container that has a lid on it. I put about 1/3 of the Chex in the bowl and add some powdered sugar. Stir or shake until Chex are coated with powdered sugar (remove from bowl).
Keep adding powdered sugar to each new 1/3 that you put in the bowl. Lay out some wax paper and separate each Chex and lay on the wax paper until hardened. Yummy!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and cut down	center.
Remove
yolks and mash with fork.
Add mayonnaise, mustard,
vinegar and relish until mixture forms a smooth paste.
Add	salt
and pepper to taste. Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Top with paprika.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal; toss lightly with a fork. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix dressing of oil, vinegar and spices.
Add black bean mixture (first 8 ingredients).
Correct for more herbs or cumin if needed. Chill.
Really delicious; you might want more vinegar too.

title: skillet chocolate pie
directions: Put in iron skillet with small amount of milk to mix.
Cook, adding rest of milk.
Heat until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need 1 new flowerpot with 8-inch diameter at top and 1 new garden hand spade.

title: robert's cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until done.
Drain fat.
In large casserole dish, layer half of cabbage, half of ground beef and half can of tomato sauce.
Repeat layer.
Press down into dish. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine and
stir
until moistened.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Bake	45
minutes
in a 375° oven or until crust is brown. This bread is wonderful when served under beef stew or with your favorite soup.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, using a little less water. Bake in bread pan.
Cool.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Cut ice cream block same way, 1 to 1 1/2-inches thick.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add cracker crumbs, catsup and 57 sauce to ground beef.
Add 1 cup water, chili mix, seasonings and beans.
Simmer for 35 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sneaky pete
directions: Mix together in a bowl and place in freezer.
Stir occasionally to keep from freezing solid.
When very slushy, remove from freezer and add 2 liters of Sprite or 7-Up.
Stir. Makes around a gallon.

title: pat's picante
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Salt and pepper to taste. Chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and juice of pineapple and cherries. Alternately, add all ingredients finishing with sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: country french chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine thyme, salt, garlic powder, tarragon, black pepper, bay leaf, wine, water and oil.
Prick all sides of chicken with fork tines.
Place in a shallow non-metallic tight fitting container.
Marinade torn pieces, cover to coat completely. Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.
Remove chickens from marinade. Barbecue, bake or fry chicken, basting occasionally with marinade until cooked through, 45 to 60 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lime-rum slush
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix.
Place in container and place in freezer.
Add mixer (half and half, ginger ale), when serving.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: In skillet over medium heat, brown chops in hot oil with onions, about 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup and milk.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until chops are tender.
Serve over egg noodles.
Serves 6.

title: cashew roast
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Place dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Make a hole. Put in wet ingredients.
Add nuts.
Mix well until you get dry ingredients wet.
Put in two pans.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until all blended.
Cover and refrigerate approximately 4 hours.
(Options:
Orange jello and mandarin oranges.)

title: tahitian chicken
directions: Mix salt and pepper with flour.
Dredge chicken in flour; place on greased baking dish and bake for 45 minutes in 325° oven. Mix orange juice, margarine, ginger and soy sauce; stir well. Brush over hot chicken as soon as it's done.
Return to oven and bake another 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper beef.
Brown beef in pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Add stewed tomatoes and bouillon cube.
Stir in mushrooms and celery.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes, onion, carrots and remaining seasonings.
Continue cooking for another hour or until meat is tender.
Combine cornstarch with small amount of water, add to stew.
Serves 5.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook frozen broccolets according to package directions; drain. Place broccolets in buttered baking dish, 8 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2-inches. In separate bowl, stir together soup and grated cheese.
Gradually add mayonnaise, milk and beaten egg to soup mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccolets.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle evenly over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in oil.
Add next 10 ingredients. Simmer uncovered.
Stir occasionally 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed.

title: french mustard dressing
directions: In a bowl, combine vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add garlic and mustard.
Finally, add oil and whisk until well blended.
If desired, you may add 1 finely chopped cooked egg to dressing.

title: caramelized bacon
directions: Press each slice into brown sugar.
Spray broiler pan.
Put bacon on broiler pan.
Cook at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: mound bars
directions: Roll and dip in chocolate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; cook squash and onion in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream. Add drained squash and carrot.
Do not mash squash.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine.
Spread 1/2 stuffing on bottom of 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture on top.
Sprinkle remainder of stuffing over squash mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: herb-cheese croutons
directions: Slice bread 3/8 inch thick.
Combine oil, butter and garlic. Toss with bread.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle on bread and toss.
Bake on a sheet 5 minutes at 400°.
Turn and bake 2 - 5 minutes.
Cool and store in air-tight container 3 weeks.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well. Add oil and beat.
Sift dry ingredients several times. Add apples, nuts and dry ingredients to oil mixture.
Beat well. Bake in greased tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: lettuce, orange and onion salad
directions: Break lettuce into bits.
Slice oranges and onion.
Squeeze some orange juice into dressing.
Add sugar.
Pour dressing over salad.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 4 hours. Shape into walnut size balls. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 72.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in an airtight container. Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: texas iced tea
directions: Mix tea, water and chopped mint.
Refrigerate 30 minutes. Strain.

title: railroad sweet and sour beef
directions: Dredge steak in flour.
Brown on all sides in small amount of oil.
Combine water, catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire, salt and onion.
Add mixture to steak.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Garnish with pimento or parsley. Serve over rice or cooked noodles.
Serves 6.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries, pineapple; Save 2 c. juice, or add water to make 2 cups. Bring juice to boiling and pour over jello, stirring until completely dissolved. When cool add coke. Stir and chill in refrigerator until partly congealed. Add drained cherries, pineapple and nuts. Pour into mold which has been rinsed in cold water. May serve with sour cream or whipped cream.

title: deluxe apple tart(10 servings)
directions: Early in Day:
In bowl, stir flour, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening, until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, mix in 2 tablespoons cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until pastry holds together, adding more water, 1 teaspoon at a time, if needed.
Pat pastry into bottom and up side of 9-inch tart pan with removal bottom. Refrigerate.

title: apricot nectar rum cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and apricot nectar.
Add cake mix.
Beat for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
In a small pan, melt margarine, sugar and rum.
As soon as cake is done, remove from oven and pour rum mixture over cake.
Allow to cool one hour before removing from pan.
Serves 16.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour in greased loaf pan or 1-pound coffee can.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots.
Slice thinly and cook just until crisp and tender; drain.
Add pepper and onions.
Mix remaining ingredients until blended and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight. This will keep well in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Marinade may be used as a salad dressing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease and deep fry.

title: lemonade iced tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Let steep for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Add cold water to make 2 quarts of tea.

title: corned beef o'brien
directions: In frypan, cook onion and green pepper in butter/margarine 5 minutes.
Add hash.
Heat, stirring occasionally until mixture is crisp and brown as desired.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover pan.
Heat 5 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: aunt jeanie's cheese potatoes
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix potatoes, cheese, sour cream, soup and green onions.
Put in oven casserole.
Mix butter and corn flakes and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar together well.
Pour over other ingredients and toss.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1/2 box Stove Top stuffing (cornbread or herb).
Put in a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Add other 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream margarine with peanut butter.
Add vanilla and sugar. Roll into balls.
Melt paraffin in double boiler and add chocolate chips.
Using a toothpick, dip each ball into the mixture and lay it on wax paper to dry.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: In top of a double boiler melt chocolate, add milk and stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows, stir until smooth and cool mixture.
In the bottom of each pie crust spread vanilla ice cream (could substitute another flavor).
Top with cooled mixture. May sprinkle chopped nuts.
Freeze overnight before serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Saute in salad oil until brown and tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion (sliced and separated), garlic salt and ginger.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add green pepper strips during last 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce; add to meat and cook until thickened.
Add tomato quarters and cook, covered, for 3 minutes.
Serve with rice or egg noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Thinly slice Longhorn cheese.
Layer in greased casserole dish chilies, cheese, chilies, cheese, etc.
Mix eggs, flour, salt, pepper, baking powder and milk and pour over layered chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sunny sprouts
directions: Cook vegetables in water with salt and sugar until tender. Drain.
Mix mustard, butter and pepper.
Spoon over vegetables.

title: snack mix
directions: Toss together cereals and popcorn in a large bowl.
Stir together oil, Worcestershire, basil, onion salt and garlic salt in a small bowl.
Pour over cereal-popcorn mixture.
Toss gently until well coated.
Place mixture in a large baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 250° oven, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Put 1 cup of eggnog in small pan.
Sprinkle gelatin over it and let stand 5 minutes, then heat until gelatin dissolves.
In meantime, put rest of eggnog in blender.
When gelatin is dissolved, pour into bowl or pan and fold in 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell or shells and use rest of Cool Whip to top just around the edge.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Stir until dissolves.
Chill for 25 minutes or until thick. Add all remaining ingredients to the jello mixture.
Spoon into mold or dish.
Chill overnight.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion and green pepper and mushrooms.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, pepper, olives, pepperoni and Italian seasoning.
Mix with macaroni.
Add cheese and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Oven: 375°.
Let butter come to room temperature.
Cream with shortening, sugars and peanut butter.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips. Refrigerate dough at least 2 hours before baking.
Place heaping tablespoon on cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: granny's candied pickles
directions: Mix and cover cucumbers and salt with boiling water and leave for 3 days in a non-metal container.
Drain, wash and cover with boiling water again and leave for 24 hours.
Then wash several times.
Mix alum, vinegar and ginger and add to the cucumbers and simmer for 1 hour.
Wash and put cucumbers in a pan with sugar, 2 1/2 pints vinegar and pickling spices.
Boil 10 minutes and can.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Make batter of flour, milk and sugar.
Pour over melted butter.
Spoon peaches over the batter and juice too.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.

title: brisket
