directions: Day One: Rinse meat well. Combine 16 ounces sauce, water, onions and seasonings in large pot on top of stove. Place brisket in pot, fat side up (should be almost covered). Cook until it starts to boil, then lower heat to medium. Add sauce if needed and cook for 2 1/2 hours. Let stand 45 minutes. Slice against the grain on an angle in thin pieces. Put slices back in pot and let sit for 3 hours. Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: salad turkey
directions: Mix altogether and chill.
Use as many or as few nuts as you want.
Serve on lettuce leaf with a dash of paprika.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Boil sugar, salt, vinegar and celery seed until it foams. Then add 3/4 cup oil and mix.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake at 375° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: crab meat hors d'oeuvres loaf
directions: Heat soup.
Dissolve gelatin and water in hot soup.
Cool slightly.
Combine with other ingredients.
Put in loaf or fish mold.
Chill in refrigerator at least overnight.
Decorate with olive slices (optional), lemon, parsley, etc.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Add pineapple, onion and pepper.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lomi salmon
directions: Shred salmon with finger; place in bowl.
Add onions and tomatoes.
Press (lomi) or mash slightly with fingers.
Put ice cubes on top.
Refrigerate.
Serve in small side dishes with some of the liquid.
Serves 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix,
then put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and refrigerate overnight.	Top
with
1 1/2 cups crushed potato chips, 1 cup Cheddar cheese (grated) and 2/3 cup toasted almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter and press into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, 1 cup of Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Mix peach glaze, peaches and Peach Schnapps (to taste) and spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: thick tomato juice
directions: Use a 7-quart cannerful of tomatoes or as many as you have. Rinse tomatoes and scald them in boiling water.
Peel, cut and remove core.
Place in canner.
Squeeze tomatoes with your hand. Bring to a boil and stir until tomatoes cook up.
Strain and put in quart jars.
Add 1 teaspoon canning salt to top of jar and seal.
Place in canning pressure cooker for 10 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: seven-up apple dumplings
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and cinnamon.
Add Seven-Up and bring to a boil.
Roll biscuits thin and wrap around apples.
Place apples in baking dish or pan.
Pour the mixed 4 ingredients over the wrapped apples.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are done.

title: spinach balls for a crowd
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place on greased baking sheets. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 20 doz.

title: deer steak
directions: Roll meat in flour with pepper.
Spray dish with Pam spray. Place meat inside; top with sliced onion.
Pour Wicker's sauce around edges of meat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until tender.

title: french pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Roll out vanilla wafers.
Put 1/2 of crumbs in greased bowl.
Pour mixture of sugar, butter and eggs over crumbs.
Add whipped cream or Cool Whip, then pineapple.
Add rest of crumbs.
Top with nuts. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: working woman's sweet potato casserole
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Spread apple filling on bottom of pan.
Drain yams and pour over apples.
Top with cherry pie filling and lightly sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into a medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir 1 cup of the Oreo cookies and all of the "rocks" into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust. Sprinkle with remaining Oreo cookies.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
*Rocks can be any combination of chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, peanut butter chips, marshmallows, granola chunks, ground nuts or any other goodie from the pantry.

title: moma's spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix together in large pan with cooked sausage, Ragu and Prego.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Put oil in thick iron pot over medium heat.
When hot, stir in flour and continue to stir until a deep brown color, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Make jello according to directions.
Add juices and fruit; fold in Cool Whip.
Wait until set, but not firm.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain corn, peas, chestnuts and pimento.
Slice or chop green pepper, onion and celery.
Marinate vegetables several hours or overnight in oil, vinegar, water, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper. Drain before serving.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in all butter except enough to roll cracker crumbs.
Spray 13 x 9 pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan; cook for 45 minutes at 350°. Add cracker crumbs; let brown.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Mix raisins with boiling water; stir and set aside.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and pork and beans until beans are broken.
Add flour and rest of dry ingredients to bean mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drain and add raisins; stir to mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes. Try it, you'll like it.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Place the watermelon rind in a large stainless steel pan. Cover with 1/2 cup of the salt and enough water to cover.
Let soak overnight.
Drain and rinse well.
Return the rind to the pan and add the 8 cups of water and the remaining tablespoon of salt. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat and simmer for about 15 minutes, until the rind is tender.
Drain and place the rind in ice water to stop the cooking process.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: In 9 x 12 dish, spread beans. Mix lemon juice, salt, pepper and mayonnaise. Spread over beans. Sprinkle taco seasoning. Layer remaining ingredients in listed order. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spinach salad
directions: This salad is most delicious when made a day in advance and marinated overnight.
Actual preparation time: about 30 minutes.

title: centennial cake(taken from 1890 cookbook, "the royal baker")
directions: Dredge fruit well with a little of the flour.
Mix rest of flour, salt and baking powder.
Rub butter and sugar together well.
Add beaten yolks, nutmeg and wine.
Beat in alternately the milk and the flour.
Whip the whites and add to mixture; beat hard.
Stir in prepared fruit.
Line 2 loaf pans with 3 thicknesses of paper.
Have cookstove fire at moderate temperature.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: shrimp felicia
directions: In a saucepan, place oil; heat to medium.
When oil is warm, put in onions, garlic and green pepper.
When onions are transparent, put in sauce.
Add 1 can water and sugar.
As it starts to bubble, throw in the salt, pepper, crushed pepper and Vigo yellow seasoning mix.
Stir well.
Add the olives.
When mixture is hot and bubbly, throw in the shrimp; stir and cook until shrimp are done.
By this time, the sauce will be thick. Serve over rice.

title: sticker glue (for children)
directions: Combine the ingredients together.
Use a paint brush to apply the glue mixture to the backs of pre-decorated cutouts or sticker designs.
Lick the backs or moisten them with a damp sponge.

title: apple nut surprise
directions: Cream eggs and sugar; add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in 2 greased 10-inch pie pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in wedges and serve with Cool Whip.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower and broccoli.
Mix other ingredients and add to vegetables; stir well.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir carrots, buttermilk or yogurt, orange juice, warm honey, oil, eggs, raisins and sunflower seeds together in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 325°.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Sift together cocoa, salt, soda and flour. Add to zucchini, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Stir in l cup pecans, pineapple, onions and salt.
Chill well.
Form into ball and roll in l cup chopped pecans.
Chill until time to serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat down rolls in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan. Place apples in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Put on top of apples.
Bake 30 minutes until tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cut raw meat from chicken breast and remove skin.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar and salt.
Add beaten eggs, margarine and milk.
Bake, covered, 30 to 40 minutes in a pan of hot water at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix shortening with flour until it resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk and blend well.
Fold until dough leaves sides of bowl. Put onto lightly floured surface and knead 4 to 6 strokes.
Roll into rectangle shapes.
Spread butter over dough, leaving a narrow margarine on all sides.
Combine sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon (all of this must be combined in a different bowl).
Sprinkle over butter.
Add raisins.

title: french or spanish rum bananas
directions: Saute halved bananas in butter.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to saucepan.
Saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Put 1 scoop of good vanilla ice cream on dish.
Place bananas next to ice cream; pour sauce over ice cream and bananas.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Enjoy!

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Combine chips and cook 6 to 7 minutes on 50% power.
Stir once.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: crazy chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Thoroughly coat chicken with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, brush once or twice during baking.

title: colcannon
directions: Boil the potatoes and mash.
Add milk and scallions (should be scalded to keep tops green) and beat until fluffy.
Toss the cooked cabbage (finely chopped) gently in the melted butter.
Add to the potatoes, together with parsley.
Fold well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana malt
directions: Slice banana; puree with other ingredients in blender.
Makes 1 serving.

title: pan coat(instead of greasing and flouring cake pans)
directions: For each cup of flour, remove 2 tablespoons of flour and add 2 tablespoons of cornstarch.
Sift together several times.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Combine ingredients and pour onto cookie sheet (with sides). Sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: szechwan pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and cool. In a large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, honey, sesame seed, garlic, hot pepper sauce, ginger and salt.
Mix well.
Add pasta, broccoli, chicken, red pepper, snow peas, mushrooms and green onions.
Toss to coat evenly.
Cover and chill until serving time. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into balls and roll in coconut flakes. Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with pineapple.
Add to yogurt, then add Cool Whip.
Divide in 4 equal dishes. This equals 1 serving for diabetics.
Good for diabetics.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Before starting cake, have eggs and oleo at room temperature. Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour, salt, soda, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in coconut.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 6 ingredients. Set aside.

title: wheatberry salad
directions: Cook wheat in water until soft (1 to 2 hours).
Drain and cool. Combine cheese and pudding.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Add enough juice only to thicken pudding batter.
Fold in Cool Whip, nuts and wheat.
Chill.
Makes a large amount.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Early in the day or day before:
In a 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan, combine cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
With back of spoon or hand, pat firmly into bottom of pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Beat at high speed and gradually add 1 cup sugar until eggs stand stiff and glossy.

title: biscotti
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir extracts. Add flour, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture. Stir in almonds.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup butter and 1 egg.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl combine rosemary, parsley, salt, pepper and oil.
After loosening the skin off the chicken, spread rosemary mixture under and over the skin.
Place in a roasting pan and roast for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until chicken is golden brown and juices run clear.	Yield:	4 to 6 servings.
(I use all chicken breasts.)

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Beat eggs until stiff, then add sugar gradually.
Spread on pie.
Bake in oven at 300° about 7 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate.
Best if made the night before.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes, then covered for 30 minutes.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: Strain pineapple.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of the juice.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, pineapple, apples, grapes, celery, nuts and onion.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, juice, poppy seed, vanilla and lemon peel.
Mix well and pour over chicken mixture.
Serve over crisp greens.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add hot water.
Cook in double boiler. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add the butter or margarine.
Stir and serve warm over ice cream.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a boil; mix with first mixture.
Beat eggs in small bowl.
Add sour milk or buttermilk and vanilla and add to first mixture. Pour into a greased cookie sheet, 12 x 15-inch.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes only.
After cake has baked for 15 minutes, begin icing.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa together.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add melted margarine, then coconut and nuts.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: garlic fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a large bowl, mix soup mix with melted butter. Dip potatoes in soup mixture then bread crumbs. Spray long pan with Pam. Arrange potatoes in a single layer. Bake uncovered for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: pesto
directions: Chop nuts fine in blender or food processor.
Remove to a bowl.
Chop basil and add to nuts, blending in garlic, oil and grated cheese.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Shape rolls into pizza pan without separating.
Brown sausage well and drain.
Pour picante sauce on rolled out crust.
Crumble sausage onto rolls.
Lay frozen hash browns (uncooked) on sausage. Pour on uncooked eggs and top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 325° or until done.
Check often.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together until well blended.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine in large bowl the Bisquick, sugar, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Pour into cake pan and bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix and roll out.
Let stand until partly dry.
Cut and cook in broth until done.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place 1/3 of potatoes and onion or cheese in a deep, 6 to 8-inch baking dish.
Add seasoning to sauce and pour on potato mixture 1/3 of white sauce.
Repeat with another 1/3 of potato mixture and sauce.
Add remaining potato mixture and sauce.
Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes uncovered or longer until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat together eggs and vinegar well.
Add sugar, butter and vanilla.
Cook in microwave until thick; stir occasionally.
Cut bananas in quarters.
Dip in dressing, then into ground peanuts.

title: blackberry and cream pie
directions: Place berries in pie shell.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine sour cream, brown sugar and flour in bowl; mix well.
Pour over berries.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer, or until filling is set and crust is brown.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: meat loaf pinwheels
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, 1/2 of cheese, egg and salt.
Mix lightly; pat out flat meat mixture to cover a 12 x 10-inch rectangle of foil.
Combine rest of cheese, rice and parsley; spread over meat.
Roll up, starting at narrow end.
Wrap securely; refrigerate several hours (or overnight).
Cut roll into 8 slices; place in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: new year's day soup
directions: Cook peas with seasoning.
Add vegetables and cook until the vegetables are tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until peas are tender.
Serve over rice.
May use turkey ham (diced) instead of ham hock.

title: orange loaf cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt, orange rind and egg yolks to butter and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add alternately the orange juice and sifted flour and baking powder. Lastly, fold in stiffly whipped egg whites.
Pour into loaf pan lined with greased wax paper.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs with 1 stick butter; press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix the sugar with 2 sticks butter and 2 eggs; blend together and beat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Spread over cracker crust.
Layer the sliced bananas over filling.
Put pineapple (well drained) over nest.
Put Cool Whip over all.
Top with cherries and sprinkle nuts last.
Refrigerate 7 hours.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Place pecans on cookie sheet; spray with cooking oil.
Spray and sprinkle with salt.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove and stir every 5 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: tillie's zucchini bread
directions: Beat zucchini, eggs, oil, and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar and milk. Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shell.
Freeze for one hour before serving.
Yield: Makes 1 pie.

title: granny's banana nut bread
directions: Take 2 peces of braede.
Put chese in the metll of the braede. Take a spoon of boter.
Take a frine pene ane it is brown, then flep it over.
Win it is brown you can eat it.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Press all but 1/2 cup of this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice the vanilla ice cream into 3/4 to 1-inch thick slices.
Arrange slices on crumbs. Smooth top of ice cream (it gets soft).
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Freezes well.
This is super fast and no baking!

title: new england clam chowder(howard johnson's)
directions: Cook clams and onions in chicken base.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
Don't brown; cook approximately 10 minutes.
Combine flour and butter with clams and onions.
Add milk and potatoes. Simmer gently until potatoes are soft.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Shape meat into patties and brown. Pour dry onion soup mix over patties. Pour mushroom soup over patties and add 1/2 can of water. Cover and cook until done. Add more water, if needed.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, bell pepper, onion, cream cheese and 1/2 cup salsa in saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted. Stir process cheese spread and milk in saucepan on low heat until smooth. Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla and roll up. Place seam side down in a lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Pour cheese sauce over tortillas; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Pour remaining salsa over tortillas.

title: flank steak and snow peas
directions: Cut steak into 2-inch strips; mix cornstarch and soy sauce; set aside.
Heat chicken stock; set aside.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet or wok until very hot.
Add garlic; cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add beef; saute quickly, keeping it moving just until it loses color (30 seconds).
Add onion and salt and pepper to taste, stirring constantly for another half minute or so.
Add chicken broth; bring quickly to a boil.
Add cauliflower, a few at a time. Cook 3 minutes.
Add snow peas, stirring constantly for another few minutes.
After 7 minutes maximum, cauliflower should be tender and pea pods should be bright green.
Add soy sauce mixture.
Mix throughly; stir until thickened.
Turn into a serving dish.
Serves 6.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove chicken from bones and tear into pieces.
Heat cream of chicken soup with milk.
Pour soup into large casserole dish.
Put a little chicken and some cheese on large end of crescent roll and roll up, pinching ends closed. Put crescent rolls into casserole dish in soup mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Stir together all ingredients (except margarine).
Stir only 1/2 melted margarine into mixture.
Top mixture with breadcrumbs or corn flakes.
Pour remaining butter on top.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Cut cheese into strips and stuff into peppers.
Beat egg whites and salt until very stiff.
Combine egg yolks and flour until mixed.
Fold in egg whites.
Dip chilies into batter and fry in oil, turning once, until brown and eggs are set.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and oleo.
Mix well. Press 1/2 of mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup walnuts and chocolate chips over crust.
Pour caramel mixture, spreading to edges of pan.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mixture.
Press gently into caramel.
Sprinkle with rest of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch; boil until clear.
Add jello and stir.
Cool.
Pour over berries.
Refrigerate.
Can use other jello flavors and berries (example: raspberry jello and raspberries).

title: helen's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: termite lodge venison marinade
directions: Combine ingredients in a mixing bowl and stir well.
Pour over venison steaks or chops in a large bowl and marinate for a few hours in a refrigerator.
Marinade also can be brushed on while grilling.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Crush crackers, add poppy seed.
Line casserole dish with half of mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Mix sour cream, soup and chicken.
Pour over cracker crumbs in dish.
Then sprinkle the rest of cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with rest of margarine.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned southern spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees, put butter into dish and place in oven to get hot.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low.

title: spanish salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets in pressure cooker for 15 minutes. Let cool and peel.
Peel and cook carrots.
Slice and let cool in strainer.
Mix all ingredients, except peas.
Add peas last.

title: tropical fruit pops
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender, food processor or mash by hand.
Fill the ingredients in 6-ounce paper cups or plastic juice pop holders.
Place 1 wooden popsicle stick in each.
Place in freezer.
Enjoy!

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients. Stir yeast mixture and buttermilk into dry ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter and brush tops with butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
To freeze, bake at 400° for about 5 to 6 minutes; cool and wrap for freezing.

title: weight watchers chive-cheese potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 1-quart casserole; add 1/2 cup water.
With vented cover, microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes, until tender. Drain potatoes; cover and set aside.
In 2-cup measure, combine milk cheese and chives.
Microwave on High 2 minutes, stirring once.
Remove from oven and stir until cheese melts.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes.
With electric portable mixer, beat until creamy.
Each serving provides 1 B, 35 calories per serving; 146 Cal, 5 g. pro, 2 g fat, 28 g car, 85 mg sod, 6 mg chol.
Serves 4.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add flour and milk alternately. (Note: Use no baking powder or soda.) Blend in flavoring and mix well. Add one egg at a time; beat well after each egg. Bake in well-greased and floured large tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until toothpick removes clean from center of cake.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in tightly covered container. Makes 2 cups mix.
One rounded teaspoonful for each individual serving.
One-third cup mix makes 1 quart of hot drink.

title: apple cake
directions: Break eggs over apples.
Mix with fork and add sugar, nuts, cinnamon and oil.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add to apple mixture and stir in vanilla.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
This will freeze well.

title: broccoli casserole #2
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, onion flakes and cheese.
Set aside. Cook broccoli and drain.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
This goes well with holiday meals; a family favorite!

title: plum nut jam
directions: To prepare fruit: Pit (do not peel) 2 1/2 pounds of fully ripe plums.
Chop very fine.
Measure 4 cups in a large saucepan.
Add orange juice and orange rind and mix well.
Add chopped nuts. Then make the jam.

title: crescent wrapped cheese
directions: Cut cheese round in half crosswise to form two circles.
Remove wax.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place one rectangle on top of second.
Repeat with remaining rectangles, making two double thick rectangles.
Press each into a 6-inch square.
Place cheese circle in center of each. Pull corners of dough to top center of cheese.
Press dough tightly against cheese.
Twist dough in center to seal.
Repeat to make second cheese wrap.
Press out excess dough.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water to "string a hair stage" and add butter to melt.
Add milk slowly (keep boiling).
Cook back to soft ball stage.
Pour over popped corn and stir until completely covered.
Shape into balls.
Store in airtight container.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Mix together.
Makes 20 (5 ounce) servings.

title: corn-in-the-husk(microwave)
directions: Discard soiled outer portion of husk.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Follow directions on the back of the Knorr vegetable soup mix box. Serve with tortilla chips or bread crisps.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add liquid fruit pectin. Add a few drops green food coloring.
Put in small jars as it has a tendency to sugar when left open or unsealed for a long time. Serve with crackers and cream cheese.

title: tangy ground beef patties and zucchini
directions: Shape ground beef into 4 plump, round patties.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix wine, shallot, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, sugar, thyme and pepper. Gradually beat in oil.
Pour over beef patties.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute onions in margarine 20 minutes.
Add chilies and chicken.
In double boiler, melt cheese, tomato juice and condensed milk.
In casserole dish, make layer of chicken mixture, then tortilla chips, then cheese sauce.
Make at least 2 layers and cover with tortilla chips.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven until bubbly hot.
It freezes well.

title: roast turkey
directions: Thaw turkey, if necessary.
Remove parts from cavities.
Rinse and pat dry.
Preheat oven to 425°.

title: onda's ham loaf
directions: Beat eggs with fork and add onions, sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Add milk to moisten.
Add bread crumbs, ground ham and pork.
Put into two loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: top-of-stove meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix beef, crumbs, 1/4 cup soup, onion, egg and seasonings.
Shape firmly into 2 loaves; brown on both sides in skillet in shortening.
Cover and cook over low heat 25 minutes. Spoon off fat.
Take remaining soup and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour on loaves and top with cheese slices.
Cook 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk together until smooth.
Stir in soup mix, garlic salt and sauces to taste.
Add salad dressing and shrimp last.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: sauteed spinach
directions: Saute garlic in a large skillet until brown.
Discard garlic. Add spinach to garlic oil; sprinkle with salt and stir-fry for 3 to 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix, heat and serve over chicken or ribs.

title: croquettes
directions: Prepare Thick White Sauce.
Stir in meat, 1 tablespoon minced onion and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Divide mixture into 12 equal parts and shape each into a ball.
Beat egg and water until blended.
Dip each ball into the egg mixture, then roll in bread crumbs until well coated. Cover and chill again for about 2 hours.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat separately egg yolks and whites.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to yolks while beating.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to whites after beating them very stiffly.
Mix whites with yolks.
Stir in cream, milk and then bourbon.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve very cold.
Sprinkle a tiny amount of nutmeg on top of each serving.
Yields 5 pints.

title: barbecue pig tail
directions: Put pig tails in roaster pan with onion, celery, green pepper, vinegar, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Cover pan with water. Put in oven at 350° until very tender.
Pour off all liquid. Add barbecue sauce and hot chili pepper.
Bake with lid off pan for 10 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil. Cool. Combine with the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well. May add 2 or 3 tablespoons mayonnaise, if desired.
Chill.
Keeps in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine milk, butter, cocoa, sugar, and vanilla in sauce pan. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook for 1 minute (do not stir).
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or spread in a buttered pyrex dish and cut into squares.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
In saucepan, melt margarine; add brown sugar, pecans and 1/4 cup pineapple juice. Stir well and pour into long deep dish or baking pan.
Arrange one can sliced pineapple (drained), decorated with 2 cherries in each ring.
In between slices, arrange one can crushed pineapple (drained).

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach of excess moisture; finely chop and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir in soup mix, mixing well.
Fold in spinach, other chopped vegetables and seasonings.

title: creme de brie soup
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart heavy saucepan. Add wine; reduce until almost dry.
Add flour; work into a paste over low heat.
Add chicken broth; heat to boiling.
Stir in bay leaf.
Cook until soup consistency is achieved.
Add whipping cream and thyme; return to heat.
Blend in small chopped pieces of Brie, slowly using whisk; whip until smooth.
Add sherry, salt and pepper; combine.
Pour into bowls.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Cover with sliced Brie.
Brown under broiler.
Serves 6.
Serve immediately.

title: mee-maw after church stew
directions: Place meat in 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil. Top with celery, carrots, potatoes and onions. Combine soup with water. Pour over meat and vegetables. Cover and bake in slow 300° to 350° oven for 3 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter reese cup cookies
directions: Spoon out cookies from roll and form into a ball.
Place a ball into each cup of the pan.
Bake as directed on the package of the cookies.
Remove from the oven and push slightly, 1 miniature cup into each cookie.
Allow to cool before removing from the pan.

title: cheesy peach pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Then add Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour over pie crust.
Let set.
Then top with pie filling.
Chill before serving.

title: peanutty broccoli slaw
directions: *Broccoli slaw mix is a prepared mix of chopped broccoli and a little carrot and red cabbage for color.

title: chicken pie
directions: Melt butter in pan for pie.
In a bowl, mix broth and soup and pour in pan with butter.
Mix flour and milk and pour over chicken. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: butterscotch chip cake
directions: Combine the brown sugar, baking soda, white sugar, flour and margarine; reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Add the buttermilk and vanilla to the mixture; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle reserved mixture on batter, chopped nuts and chips. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand or with mixer.
Fill burrito shells; roll.
Do not fold ends inside.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch sections and serve.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, then pour into 1 large or 2 small casserole dishes. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° to 375° for about 30 minutes. Remove foil. Add more cheese on top and melt.

title: clam chowder
directions: Strain broth of steamed quahogs or use 2 bottles of clam juice.
Add water to juice or broth.
Bring quahogs or clams, broth or clam juice, onions, potatoes, salt, pepper, shortening or fried salt pork to a boil.
Lower heat and cook for 1 hour until potatoes are soft.
Chowder may be eaten as is or with added ingredients to make milk chowder or Manhattan.
If adding tomato sauce or milk, cook another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage salad(est. 175 people)
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots, onions and peppers or pineapple and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together and add to cabbage.
Stir together and salt and pepper to taste.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together (except Ritz crackers) and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Top with enough crushed Ritz cracker crumbs to cover.
Butter top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: deviled ham ball
directions: Mix deviled ham, cream cheese, Ranch dressing and crushed pineapple in a large bowl.
After you get it well blended, shape mixture into a ball.
Roll ball in the grated cheese.
Allow ball to chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: fruit dip
directions: Add milk to make good dip consistency.
Add food coloring.

title: love that salsa(toss together in 5 minutes)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving. Store, covered, for up to a week.
Great with chips and fajitas.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring frequently. Drain off fat.
Saute onion and green pepper in saucepan until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add to ground beef. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Crush wafers; mix with melted butter using fork.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch spring-form pan, leaving a 1-inch space at top.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add melted chocolate chips.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add sour cream; mix until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.
After cooling, garnish with chocolate shavings.

title: mushroom chicken(k'ou mo chi ting)
directions: Dredge uncooked chicken meat (cut in 1-inch squares) with a mixture of soy sauce, sugar and cornstarch.
Put mushrooms in a saucepan over low heat.
When it boils, add the dredged chicken. Gradually add the soup stock and cook until chicken is tender. Serve hot with rice.
Serves 6.

title: quick veggie soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cook ground beef in a nonstick skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir meat into vegetable mixture; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients well and press on sides and bottom of baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let this cool.

title: katy's oven stew
directions: Marinate beef in sherry wine and French dressing (if desired). Mix sugar, salt and barley with tomatoes.
Combine rest of ingredients. Cover and bake at 300° for 5 hours.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut crosswise into 1/8-inch slices.
Combine with onions in large crock or nonmetallic container.
Dissolve salt in water; pour over vegetables.
Weight vegetables down with a plate almost as large as the crock.
Lay a large jar filled with water on plate to keep vegetables under brine; let stand 2 hours. Combine sugar and remaining ingredients in large saucepot; bring to boil.
Remove garlic.
Drain vegetables; add to hot syrup; heat just to boiling.
Simmer while quickly packing 1 clean, hot jar at a time.
Fill to within 1/2-inch of top, making sure vinegar solution covers vegetables.
Cap each jar at once.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs two at a time, beating after each time.
Add flavorings.
Sift flour over cut up fruit and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter over this and mix well.
Line two tube pans with well-greased brown paper and divide the batter into them.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: molded shrimp salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Add vinegar and sugar. Stir over boiling water to dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise until blended.
Add shrimp, eggs, celery, pimento and pepper to gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold and chill until firm. Unmold on salad greens.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste of 2 Chronicles 9:9, 6 Jeremiah 17:11, 1/2 cup Genesis 24:20, pinch of Leviticus 2:13 and 2 tablespoons Amos 4:5, then follow Solomon's advice for making good boys (Proverbs 24:14).

title: cake
directions: You will also need a fluted microwave Bundt pan or microwave-safe pan.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Beat together, egg, oil and milk in medium-sized bowl (use wire whip).
Add biscuit mix, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts.
Beat briskly with spoon until well mixed.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Bake on pan with rack at about 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: mrs. mabry's cake
directions: Beat about 2 minutes.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) cake pans at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or in 3 (7-inch) cake pans for 20 to 25 minutes. Allow to cool before frosting/icing.

title: party chicken and shrimp
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Saute chicken in onion drippings until browned.
In a large pot, put chicken, onion and everything else, but shrimp.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover and simmer 5 minutes until tender.
Can serve over rice if wanted.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with 2 1/2 cups lukewarm water. Mix in flour and let rise about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick sausage and rice
directions: In a large skillet brown sausage, peppers and onion in butter; remove.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni in the skillet according to directions on the boxes.
Ten minutes before rice is done, add sausage, pepper and onion to Rice-A-Roni.
Cook remaining time and serve hot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: To the beaten egg, add sugar and melted butter (butter must be cool).
Add bananas and stir well.
Add flour, soda, salt and chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased pan for 45 minutes at 375°. Cover and let stand overnight.
Delicious.

title: new orleans style jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in melted butter.
Add shrimp and ham; fry for 5 minutes on medium heat. Stir in tomatoes and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Stir in rice and add seasoning.
Add 1 cup water and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer until rice is done, about 30 minutes.

title: dot's black beans and rice
directions: Wash beans thoroughly and soak overnight in water.
Use this water for cooking.
Fry slightly onion, green peppers and garlic in olive oil.
Combine all ingredients, except the vinegar, which is added a few minutes before beans are ready to serve.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer and cook until the beans are tender and the liquid is thick.
Serve over white or yellow rice or in a soup bowl.
Chopped white onions may be added to top before serving.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix all and pour into 9-inch square pan.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Combine with cooked noodles and next three ingredients in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat and add vanilla; stir.
Serve over ice cream.

title: stuffed spinach casserole
directions: Let dough rise to twice frozen size.
Divide into thirds. Preheat oven to 400°.
Pat 1/3 of dough into bottom and sides of baker (9 x 9-inch).
Layer half of Mozzarella on top of dough; top with mixture of spinach, mushrooms and onions.
Top with remaining Mozzarella.
Roll out another 1/3 of dough into 9-inch square. Place on top; pinch sides together to seal sides to top.
Spread pizza sauce and Parmesan over top; bake 10 minutes more.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: apple snack squares
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, eggs and oil. Mix well. Stir in flour and cinnamon (batter will be thick). Stir in apples and nuts. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with chips. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Cool before cutting. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: party time potato slices
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Mix together sour cream and chives. Lightly brush both sides of potatoes with margarine and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil 5 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.
Top potatoes with Velveeta and bacon.
Continue broiling until cheese spread begins to melt.
Serve with sour cream mixture.
Makes about 2 dozen.
Preparation time:
15 minutes; cooking time:
12 minutes.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blanch rhubarb in hot water; drain and put in unbaked crust. Add beaten eggs to sugar and flour.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish that has been buttered.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: o'brien hot dish
directions: Dice the potatoes which have been boiled with the skins on. Put ham, green pepper, onion and potatoes in casserole.
Make white sauce with flour, butter and milk.
Add cheese to sauce and allow to melt.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: white chile
directions: In large saucepan, combine water, lemon pepper and cumin seed. Bring to a boil.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.
Remove chicken and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Return to pan.

title: spinach salad with variety
directions: Combine and toss all ingredients with honey or orange based dressing or your desired dressing.

title: date delight
directions: Beat first three ingredients together and add next three ingredients.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and cut into bars.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Mix all at one time.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes. Makes 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/2 can or 1/3 cup milk.
Pour half into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 6 minutes exactly.
While baking, melt caramels and rest of milk in microwave.
After you take cake out, spread caramel over cake.*
Take rest of cake mixture and pat into small patties and lay over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes exactly.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 12 minutes.
Strain through several thicknesses of cheesecloth, squeezing gently.
Add lemon juice, orange juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Serve hot. Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: excellent blueberry squares
directions: Mix together graham crumbs, butter and brown sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, saving 1/2 cup for topping.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, white sugar, vanilla and lemon juice until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip and blueberries. Spread on top of graham cracker crust and chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine; mix all other ingredients and add pepper, onion and butter.
Mix well.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Add grated cheese to top.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Best served at room temperature.

title: red raspberry jam
directions: *You will need more raspberries if you take some or all of the seeds out.
Put raspberries through a food mill to remove some seeds or through a fine sieve to get all the seeds out.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Blend tomatoes, including liquid, until fine.
In skillet, make roux of flour and butter (over low heat).
Add garlic and continue browning until tender.
Add tomatoes, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add chopped parsley before removing from heat.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2 to 4.
Enjoy.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add the tomato soup and seasonings to taste.
Mix over heat until the cheese is melted. Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Spread on bun halves; place under broiler until brown.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in a small bowl. Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in white chips.
Drop well rounded teaspoonfuls (balls) onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
In quart jar, put dill, 2 tablespoons salt and 3 to 4 garlic cloves.
Pack cucumbers in jar.
Bring to a boil, water and vinegar.
Pour over pickles.
Seal and process in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes, until cucumbers change colors.

title: javanese curried noodles
directions: Cook the 2 1/2 cups curly broad noodles in boiling salted water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon cooking oil so the noodles won't stick together.
Place wok or skillet over low heat.
Add curry powder and heat until fragrant.
Add oil.
Increase heat; add chopped onions.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add ground beef; stir-fry until no pink remains.
Combine catsup, soy sauce, black pepper and water into a small mixing bowl.
Stir into meat mixture and heat until boiling.
Add noodles and mix well.
Add bean sprouts or finely shredded cabbage.
Stir and mix until hot.
This looks more like Indonesian fried noodles if you use Ramen noodles instead of the curly ones.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vinegar.
Sift flour and soda together.
Mix flour and buttermilk alternately with egg mixture. Add vanilla and food coloring.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake edges separate from pan (makes 3 layers).

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening.
After shortening has been creamed, add your sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk.
In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients together.
Gradually add the dry ingredients to the shortening mix.
If batter is still wet, gradually add more flour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Fry in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: spice bars
directions: Cook raisins in water until raisins are plumped, then add shortening and soda to hot water and raisins.
Mix together the flour, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, salt and nuts.
Pour raisin mixture into the flour mixture and mix together.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch sheet pan and spread mixture into it.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Spread powdered sugar icing on when cool.

title: tomato-topped fish
directions: *Fish Suggestion:
Cod, flounder, sole, whitefish or sea bass.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour and add soda; add to mixture with buttermilk.
Flour first and last. Stir in nuts and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: potato vegetable salad
directions: Boil potatoes until they are tender.
While they are cooling, steam broccoli and cauliflower about 4 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Cut carrots into thin slivers.
Slice cucumbers.
Cut potato into chunks.
Gently stir all vegetables together in a large mixing bowl.
In another bowl, whisk together yogurt, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and stir carefully until dressing coats evenly.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: chilled zucchini soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, combine zucchini, onion and curry.
Add broth.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling; cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Blend until smooth.
In a medium bowl, combine zucchini mix, half and half, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate until serving (at least 2 hours).

title: school cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well; roll into small balls.
Roll balls in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients.
In another bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients; stir until combined.
Spoon into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on rack.
Serve warm.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in covered container and chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: run for the roses punch
directions: In a 3-quart container, combine first 5 ingredients; tint green.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and cool in refrigerator.
Mix all other ingredients.
Just before serving, add beef and salad dressing.
Toss well and serve.
This is a large recipe and serves many.

title: toffee bit bars
directions: Beat butter until creamy, beat in brown sugar, vanilla, and egg yolk.
Stir in flour and 1 c. toffee bits.
Press into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 18-20 min. or until light brown.
Immediately pour choc. chips over pan and let sit 5 min., then spread evenly.
Sprinkle the remaining toffee bits on top and let set.
Cut into 2 in. squares and enjoy!

title: tahitian ham loaf
directions: Thoroughly combine first 8 ingredients.
Shape mixture into 9 patties.
(Be sure patties are no wider than pineapple slices).

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together. Cut in shortening.
Soften yeast in water and stir until dissolved.
Mix with buttermilk and combine with dry ingredients. Roll out to 1/4-inch thick and cut biscuits.
Place in cold oven.
Biscuits will rise while oven heats.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes.
These biscuits may be made up and frozen for future use.

title: soft ginger cakes
directions: Cream sugar well with margarine.
Stir soda into buttermilk. Combine the ingredients and drop on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Brush top with well beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: amish chops
directions: Mix well.
Place chops in baking dish.
Pour mixture over chops.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: sausage zuppa (sausage soup)
directions: Make day before.
In a 5-quart large pot, cook sausage over medium heat until lightly browned.
Drain off fat.
Add garlic and onions; cook until limp.
Stir in tomatoes and juice, breaking into pieces.
Add broth, wine and basil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cool, then chill.
The next day, skim off any fat. Reheat soup; add parsley, pepper and zucchini.
Simmer 25 minutes. Add hot bow tie pasta to soup bowls and ladle soup over. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Place skin side down in greased 9 x 13 dish. Combine margarine, preserves and mustard in small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth. Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, basting and turning once.

title: brown sugar caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Beat in vanilla and confectioners sugar gradually until a spreading consistency is reached.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients in a bowl and make well in center. Add all other ingredients.
Stir well until moistened.
Bake in two large well-greased loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Stir in beaten egg.
Sift flour and baking powder together and combine with egg mixture.
Add vanilla and walnuts to the batter.
Spread in an oiled 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool slightly. Cut into squares.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour over broccoli and cauliflower. Marinate several hours, stirring occasionally.

title: orange chocolate balls
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add chocolate.
Melt over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and creamy.
Add chocolate mixture, orange rind and pecans.
Chill mixture in refrigerator until set and easy to handle.
With two spoons, roll mixture into balls.
Place sprinkles on wax paper.
Roll chocolate balls in sprinkles until covered.
Let balls firm up in the refrigerator before serving.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecue corn bread
directions: In a heavy skillet, fry the sausage until lightly browned and all fat has been rendered.
Remove to drain on paper towels.
In 1 tablespoon remaining fat, saute onion until lightly browned.
Set aside.

title: best beef stew
directions: In a large pot, mix in order; stew meat, vegetables and seasonings.
Add over vegetables the tomatoes and tapioca.	Bake for one hour at 350°.
Then turn oven to 300° for three hours. Bake at least 3 1/2 hours before mixing.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring 6 c. water to boil. Add broccoli and onion. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Add cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder and stir until cheese melts. Stir in milk, half and half and margarine. Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated. Combine flour and 1/2 c. water. Stir until smooth. Gradually add to broccoli mixture, stirring constantly. Cook over medium heat until thickened. Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: sour cream crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with potato chips. Makes 2 cups.

title: mam-ma's blackberry (or strawberry) jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and
sugar in mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time. Whip well in between at high speed. Sift flour with spices and salt. Add soda to buttermilk and stir well.
Fold in flour alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Add wine last.
Fold in pecans and jam.
Pour into three 9-inch well oiled and floured pans and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes. At 30 minutes, test with straw.
When straw is clean, remove from oven. Cool in pans 5 minutes.

title: broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Melt butter; add soup, rice and frozen broccoli.
Mix.
Add melted Cheez Whiz and mix.
Put mixture into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish; sprinkle onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Blend ingredients, except ice, on lowest speed of electric blender.
Add ice cubes, one at a time, while machine is running. Blend until smooth.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in electric blender for 3 minutes on high.
Pour into 10 1/2-inch greased pie dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not open oven until done.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice
directions: Mix.
Place in a 10 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup of shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Freezes well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients (except tomato sauce) and mix with hands. Form into loaf. Top with tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: prune whip(serves 6)
directions: Cook together the sugar and prune juice until candy thermometer reads 234°.
Add hot syrup slowly to egg whites while continuing to beat.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Add prunes; continue beating until mixture holds its shape.
Serve with Custard Sauce.

title: apple surprise
directions: Melt butter in deep skillet or baking dish.
Mix next 4 ingredients into a batter and pour onto melted butter.
Drain fruit; add spices and spoon onto batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until batter covers fruit and browns.
Fruit settles to bottom and cake rises to top and makes a delicious, moist dessert. Serve plain or topped with cream.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together.
Let set at least 4 hours to blend flavors. Serve on crackers.

title: sun-dried tomato and basil dip
directions: Blend until smooth in blender. Serve with fresh vegetables. Keeps up to 4 days in fridge.
Freshen with lemon juice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate the zucchini. Beat eggs. Add sugar, vanilla and oil. Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture. Add zucchini. Fold in nuts. Bake in greased and floured loaf or tube pan for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 medium loaves.

title: orange roughy
directions: Center tin foil 2 times size of pan.
Lay half the butter on foil.
Arrange fillets in a single layer on top of butter and place remaining butter on top of fillets.
Add Mrs. Dash, juice of half a lemon, bread crumbs and almonds.
Close foil to the top and fold over.
Bake 25 minutes at 375° or until fish is tender and flaky.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes with foil open and brown bread crumbs slightly.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage until done, stirring to crumble.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine sausage and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a well greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Refrigerate, covered overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lonie chappell's smoky beans
directions: In skillet, combine onion, green pepper and salad oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and simmer about 5 minutes, if necessary, to reduce liquid.

title: chicken or squid luau
directions: Drain liquid from coconuts into bowl.
Crack shell, remove white meat and grate.
Measure 4 cups reserved coconut liquid (adding water, if necessary).
Pour over grated coconut and let stand 15 minutes.
Squeeze meat and juice through double thickness of dampened cheesecloth into bowl.
Set aside.
Combine chicken, 3 teaspoons salt and 3 cups water in saucepan.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Bone and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Remove stem and strip tough part of rib from washed taro leaves.
Place leaves, 1 teaspoon salt and 3 cups water in deep saucepan.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Drain and add fresh water; simmer for 1 additional hour or until bitter sting is extracted from leaves.
Squeeze to remove excess water.
Add meat and coconut milk to taro leaves.
Heat thoroughly and serve immediately.
Serves 20.

title: sour salmon dip
directions: Drain salmon; mash. Blend in salt, Tabasco sauce and onion. Add sour cream. Cover; chill. Garnish with caviar and surrounded with trimmed, quartered pumpernickel. Yields 2 cups.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first seven ingredients well.
Pour half of batter into well-greased tube pan.
Arrange a layer of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Add remaining batter on top with rest of apples. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: corned beef and cabbage salad
directions: Combine sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard, pepper, vinegar, oil and onion.
Blend thoroughly.
Combine cabbage, corned beef and green pepper in large bowl.
Add vinegar mixture; toss. Cover; refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Toss before serving; drain off excess liquid.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: eagle brand chocolate bars
directions: Melt 1 cup margarine; stir in 1/4 cup cocoa.
Add water and bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add cocoa mix and beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup Eagle Brand, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until done. In pan, melt remaining 1/4 cup margarine; stir in 1/4 cup cocoa and rest of Eagle Brand milk and powdered sugar.
Spread over warm cake.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients (except popcorn and soda) for 5 minutes. Mix well.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and add soda. Stir in quickly.
Pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Place on large pan in single layer.
Place in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir 3 to 4 times.
Store in sealed container.
May add peanuts (optional).

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Lightly salt chicken.
Place in oblong pan with 1/2 cup hot water.
Place
in
oven
and	cook 15 minutes before adding sauce.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend all ingredients except crab meat and 1/2 cup of Cheddar cheese in food processor.
Fold in crab meat and put in serving dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with remaining cheese and paprika.
Serve with mild crackers.

title: sour cream cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm water in a large mixing bowl, let stand
5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream, 1/2 cup margarine, 1/4
cup sugar, eggs, salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 1 1/2 cups
flour and
beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour, cover
and refrigerate
hours.
Roll
dough out to an 18 x 15-inch rectangle,
combine
1/4 cup margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle
over
rectangle.
Carefully
roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Cut roll into 1-inch slices.
Place in
two greased 9-inch square pans, cover and let rise in warm place about
hour.
Bake
at
for
18 to 20 minutes. Combine powdered
sugar,
milk
and
teaspoon
vanilla. Drizzle over warm rolls.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: warm cake sauce
directions: Stir over medium heat until thick.
Serve over warm cake.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring until well combined.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool loaves in pans about 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: chow chow(green tomato relish)
directions: Grind tomatoes, cabbage, peppers and onions together.
Put in bag with salt; let drip overnight.

title: onion casserole number 2
directions: Melt butter and combine with milk.
Heat.
Arrange onions in casserole dish.
Sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese; sprinkle a layer of flour, salt and pepper.
Pour milk mixture over all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot and raisin sunshine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except lettuce leaves, in a mixing bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 15 minutes; toss again before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: homestyle chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar with cocoa.
Slowly add hot water.
Heat to boil. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cool.
Refrigerate.
Serve warm or cold over your favorite dessert!

title: tuna crunch casserole
directions: Combine carrot pieces and tuna fish. Mix well. Place in casserole dish. Add rice, corn and milk; mix well. Cover and microwave on High 10 minutes. Stir halfway and stir again after cooking. Sprinkle crackers evenly on top.

title: turkey meatballs(low-fat)
directions: Tear bread; mix with milk.
Add turkey, onion, egg whites, parsley, garlic and pepper; toss to combine.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Place on broiler rack.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp cocktail spread
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Spread on plate or in a 6 x 12-inch plastic container.
Chill.
Before serving, spread 1 jar of seafood cocktail sauce on top of cheese and shrimp mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: eggs rebel recipe
directions: Put croutons and ham into a greased casserole dish. Mix all other ingredients in a blender or with a mixer and pour over the croutons and ham.
Refrigerate for 12 hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake uncovered 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix starch with cold water to form a creamy paste.
Add boiling water and cook until mixture becomes transparent or glossy looking.
Stir constantly.
Let mixture cool a bit, then add soap flakes, stirring until evenly distributed.
Let cool and pour into 8 jars with screw tops.
Stir into each jar 1/2 tablespoon powdered poster paint.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips; spoon chocolate chips in after all other ingredients are blended. Pour into lightly greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: crawfish cocktail
directions: Boil in well salted water 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Fill bowl with chopped ice and arrange tails over top.
Provide toothpicks for handy dipping.
Serve with Cocktail Sauce.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in 2 cups boiling water until tender.
Brown beef and onion; mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish. Dot with butter and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, egg and mashed beans together.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture along with apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peppy clam shells
directions: In medium skillet, cook onion, celery and green pepper in 4 tablespoons butter until tender but not brown.
Stir in flour, cheese and seasonings.
Add 1/4 cup cracker crumbs; mix well. Stir in undrained clams; cook until mixture thickens.
Divide among 4 large baking shells.
Combine the rest of the crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick of melted margarine in a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let it set.

Beat 2 sticks melted margarine, powdered sugar and egg for 15 minutes (this is very necessary). Add pinch of salt and pour over graham cracker crumb crust. Arrange sliced bananas and pineapple on top of this. Spread thawed Cool Whip on the above mixture. Sprinkle with nuts. Chill overnight.
Decorate each serving with a maraschino cherry.

title: smokies in barbecue
directions: Blend and heat first 5 ingredients.
Add sausages.
Keep warm in chafing dish.

title: swedish meatballs(simple family style)
directions: Mix ingredients together lightly; gently form into small balls (1 1/2-inch).
Brown in hot fat; add about 1/4 cup hot water. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Thicken pan gravy; flavor with beef bouillon if needed.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Cook all ingredients, except Hershey bars and paraffin, to soft ball stage, stirring to keep from sticking.
Add 3 or 4 cups chopped pecans.
Pour into greased pan and refrigerate overnight. Cut in small pieces.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Mix together soups, onion and wine.
Salt and pepper chicken. Place in large baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over it.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: minted chicken and rice soup
directions: In 1-quart shallow casserole, combine all ingredients except mint and pepper.
Microwave on High for 13 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking until chicken is tender.
Stir in mint and pepper.
Makes two 1 1/2-cup servings.
Contains 162 calories, 2 g fat and 1,064 mg sodium.

title: biscuits for two
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Turn onto floured board, knead one minute. Roll or pat dough to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with a floured 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet and bake for 10-12 minutes at 450°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix the butter, sour cream, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Add the sugar and pecans.
This is very good with peaches, strawberries, bananas, pineapple, apples, etc.

title: ice cream(homemade)
directions: Mix and put in churn.

title: the suckers from dew drop
directions: In medium saucepan, add sugar, corn syrup and half cup of water.
Cook over medium heat without stirring until candy thermometer registers 300° or until small amount
of mixture forms hard brittle threads when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Have lollipop sticks ready on flat surface; place on top of wax paper and pour mixture on top of stick and let cool.
Remove lollipops when hardened.

title: chocolate almond biscotti
directions: About 3 hours before serving:
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, toast almonds shaking skillet frequently until nuts are golden.
Cool almonds & chop.

title: chocolate marshmallow sauce
directions: Cook sugar and water in saucepan to 220°.
Remove from heat; stir in cocoa, vanilla and marshmallows until melted.
Cool, without stirring, until bottom of pan just feels warm to hand. Beat to thicken and serve warm over ice cream.
Makes 2 cups of sauce.

title: caramel corn
directions: Microwave first 4 ingredients.
Boil 2 minutes.
Take out and add soda.
Stir until very bubbly.
Pop the popcorn.
Spray inside of brown paper grocery bag with Pam.
Put popcorn and caramel in the bag and shake.
Yummy!

title: potato planks
directions: Prepare potatoes for boiling.
Cut lengthwise into eights. Set oven control to broil and/or 550°.
Place potatoes, cut side down, in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Brush with oil.

title: jennie's pound cake
directions: Mix together the jello and boiling water; let it cool.
Add cake mix, eggs, oil, lemon juice and salt.
Mix 5 minutes.
Use ungreased tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Powder with powdered sugar.
Let cool.
Pour over this the juice of 1 orange mixed with 1/2 cup sugar.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Combine peanut butter, vanilla, cereal and syrup mixture; mix well.
Pat into lightly greased pan (8 x 8-inch).
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together in double boiler.
Cover peanut butter with the melted chips.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: brownies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet 'n' sour sauce
directions: Place brown sugar and 1/2 cup water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce volume by 1/2 over high heat.
Add vinegar, pineapple juice, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 13 minutes.

title: veal and peppers
directions: Brown veal in olive oil and garlic.
Add oregano, basil, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Add additional can of tomato sauce, if desired or needed.
Cook covered on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Add sliced peppers and sliced onions and continue cooking for another 1/2 hour.
Serve over white rice.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Top with onion rings.
Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add cream cheese and onion; mix well.
Crush pecans.
Roll cheese ball in pecans.
This is best if made a day ahead.
Serve with any type of cracker.

title: spinach stuffed roast
directions: In a skillet saute mushrooms and onions in oil until tender. Stir in spinach, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, garlic powder and sage.
Untie pork roast and separate the loins.
Spread stuffing over one loin to within 1 inch of the edges.
Top with remaining loin, retie securely with a heavy string.
Place in an ungreased shallow baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until a meat thermometer reads 160 to 170 degrees.
Let stand for 15 minutes before slicing.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chicken wing sauce
directions: Cook until blended (especially mustard).
Mix well.
The longer you cook, the better it gets.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Cream butter thoroughly, then add sugar and beat well.
Put egg yolk and vanilla in and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
These melt in your mouth if eaten while still slightly warm.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: After slicing, coat potatoes with oil.
Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash Table Blend seasoning to taste.
Place on a large cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray in a single layer. Place in 450° oven until potatoes are tender and begin to brown. Makes 4 servings.
Exchanges equal 1 bread and starch.

title: pineapple cool whip cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all together.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix salt thoroughly into mixture of first 4 ingredients.
Empty ice cubes in center and let stand 3 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drain vegetables thoroughly.
Heat vinegar mixture to boiling.
Add vegetables and heat over low heat to scalding. Simmer on low for 10 minutes.
Do not allow to boil.
Stir frequently to keep from sticking.
Seal while hot.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Fry crumbled sausage and beef until cooked; drain well.
Add onion, green chilies and tomatoes.
If mixture is thin, add a tablespoon of flour.
Add Velveeta cheese to cooked mixture and melt.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Mix sauce ingredients.
Cut wieners into bite size pieces. Add to sauce.
Cook in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Add ice ring.

title: oatmeal cake frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Boil until frosting becomes bubbly. Spread evenly over cake.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients, working in shortening until size of small peas. Mix other ingredients and add to flour mixture. Refrigerate several hours.
This makes at least 4 average single pie crusts and can be kept in refrigerator several days.

title: two-cheese tossed salad
directions: In a jar with tight-fitting lid, combine the first eight ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, toss spinach, lettuce, mushrooms and cheeses in a large salad bowl. Shake dressing and pour over salad.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Yield 12-14 servings.

title: italian pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar, beating until smooth.
Add cooled margarine and flavoring.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to sugar mixture gradually.
Dough will be sticky. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto heated pizzelle iron grip.
Bake until lightly browned.
Cool on racks.
Will stay crisp stored stacked in brown grocery bag.

title: broccoli jennifer
directions: Generously butter 1-quart casserole.
Combine broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and egg.
Blend well. Turn into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and heated throughout about 35 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Cool and split in half with dental floss.
Mix condensed milk, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Spread between layers and on top.
Refrigerate.
Better if made a day ahead.

title: 10 minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly with rotary beater until mixture forms peaks, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.

title: spoon burgers(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Serve over open-faced bun.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Mix all ingredients except noodles and bring to boil.
Add noodles and cook 15 minutes at slow boil.
Can be simmered longer if desired.

title: easy spinach dip
directions: Mix all the above ingredients.
Let chill.
Carve out the center of a loaf of rye bread and fill with spinach dip.
Serve with rye bread chunks removed from center and crackers.

title: day before mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft and prepare as mashed potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate chip oat cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Stir in oats, pecans and chocolate pieces.
Drop cookies on sheet (lightly greased).
Bake in oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: old-time ginger bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients; beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add molasses and sour cream and beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Spread evenly in a 15 x 10-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce.
Arrange wedges on platter.
