Spoon shrimp mixture on top of wedges.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add sugar and flour.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix and chill. Sprinkle with pecans.
Freezes well.

title: kielke
directions: Add more milk, if necessary.
Mix into a dough and roll out in sheets.
Roll up a sheet of dough as you would a jelly roll.
Cut off short, thick noodles.
Shake them out so they do not stick together.
Drop into a kettle of boiling water and cook 5 minutes. Strain and let water run through them.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, stirring to avoid large lumps.
Add onion (1/2 cup or more); cook until clear and soft.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick and easy punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: venison roast
directions: Brown roast in butter; add salt, pepper and a few whole cloves.
Place in a pressure cooker at 10 pound pressure for 45 minutes (will not be completely done; tender).
Place onion slices over top of meat; pour cream over all roast until meat has absorbed all of cream.
Make gravy from drippings.
Can also be sliced when cold for sandwiches.

title: chinese hot and sour soup
directions: Drain all canned items.
Slice pork into tiny pieces.
Lightly brown meat in oil in 3-quart pan.
Drain and set aside.
In same pan, bring broth to boil.
Add pork, bamboo shoots, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add vinegar, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir into soup.
Stir until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Stir soup to swirl; pour beaten egg into center of swirl; cook 2 more minutes.

title: baked beans(to can)
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Cook until tender and drain. Mix all the other ingredients together; pour over beans.
Mix well.
Put into jars and cold pack for 3 hours.
Yields 18 to 19 quarts.

title: kathryn hall's pecan sandies
directions: Combine
ingredients, mix well.
Roll into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into approximately 1/3 inch thick wedges.
In a bowl, mix with olive oil, salt, black pepper, garlic powder and cumin (to taste).
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 350 degrees, turning several times until golden brown on both sides.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger, soup mix, oatmeal and egg.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in skillet.
Place in crock-pot. Add jelly and chili sauce.
Simmer on low for 2 hours.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Beat egg slightly.
Then beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into crust.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Insert knife 1-inch from side of filling to test.
If knife comes out clean, custard is done.
Center will be soft, but will set up as custard cools. Overcooking will make custard watery when cut.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake cake mix in three layers.
Combine the following in a saucepan:
marshmallows, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup sweet milk and coconut.
Cook until marshmallows melt and thicken over medium heat.
Spread between the cake layers.
Combine in another saucepan:
1 cup sugar, butter, 1/4 cup sweet milk and cocoa. Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over cake.

title: easy stew
directions: Place beef in 3 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrots and onions.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces and place in bottom of large glass bowl.
Top with chopped celery and chopped onion, then chopped mushrooms and peas.
Top with hard-boiled eggs.
Blend mayonnaise with dill weed and white pepper.
Spread over the eggs. Top with cooked shrimp, then grated cheese.
Put bacon over cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour in medium saucepan; stir in milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla, stirring well.
Pour over layer of cookies and banana (sliced).
There should be two layers.
Top with cookies.
Recipe may be doubled.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and cook in 400° oven for 45 minutes to	1
hour
or in microwave on High for 20 to 30 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes.

title: pecan dump
directions: Pour peaches and juice in casserole dish.
Spread dry cake mix over peaches.
Cut butter in thin slices on cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with Cool Whip.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Toss onion, tomatoes, and lettuce with cheese and salad dressing.
Add tortilla chips and avocado.	Add salt and beans to browned meat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add to salad.
Garnish with tortilla chips, avocado and tomato slices.	Serves 10-12.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and instant pudding until thickened. Add Eagle Brand milk. Stir to mix. Add Cool Whip.

title: cheese-baked haddock
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a large shallow baking dish.
Place fish in baking dish.
Pour lemon juice over fish and sprinkle with salt, pepper and thyme.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.

title: fried chicken supreme
directions: Use only the legs, wings, thighs and breast.
Wash and dry. Dip the pieces into flour, then in the egg, which has been slightly beaten with milk.
Dip fowl into bread crumbs.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Place cubed beef in dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir in can of cream of mushroom soup.
Cover and bake in 350° oven until beef is tender (approximately 2 hours).
Add partially cooked noodles into casserole dish with the beef/soup mixture.
Stir well.
Cover dish, then bake an additional 30 to 60 minutes.

title: microwave tapioca pudding
directions: Combine
sugar,
tapioca,
milk
and
egg
in a 2 quart microwave-safe
bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Cook at High until mixture comes to a full boil, 10 to 12 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes. Add vanilla.
Cool for 20 minutes; stir.

title: cajun popcorn
directions: Combine all spices in a cup; mix well.
Pour melted butter over warm popcorn, mixing through carefully.
Sprinkle spices over popcorn and quickly toss.

title: three week cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper, onions, carrots and sugar in large bowl; mix well.
Mix the oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir until very well mixed.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Let stand 3 days.
Flavor improves the longer it stands.
Will keep for a month in refrigerator.

title: no bake reese's cup cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with peanut butter.
Add crumbs and sugar; mix well.
Pat into an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Spread melted chocolate over top.
Refrigerate.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: homemade pound cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, then milk.
Slowly add sifted flour and baking powder.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla until combined. Gradually beat in flour, soda and salt until smooth.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes (microwave 15 minutes).

title: harvest salmon chowder
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving liquid.
Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter until vegetables are translucent.
Add potatoes, carrots, chicken broth and seasonings. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook 5 minutes. Add flaked salmon, reserving salmon liquid, evaporated milk and corn.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with sprinkling of parsley.

title: chocolate chip-cream cheese bars
directions: Let cookie dough soften at room temperature.
Spread one package of dough on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: sunshine dill pickles
directions: Heat ingredients.
Pack cleaned cucumbers, dill, garlic bud and pepper.
Pour liquid over this, seal and set in the sun for 9 (nine) days.

title: chicken salad on melon
directions: For dressing, in a blender combine sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard and salt.
Cover and blend for 5 seconds.
Through the opening in the lid on slow speed, gradually add oil in a thin stream.
Stop blender and scrape sides.
Cover and blend for 1 to 2 minutes more or until the dressing is slightly thickened.
Stir in poppy seed.

title: wedding cakes(cookies)
directions: In medium bowl, with mixer at medium speed, cream butter or margarine and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and flour; continue beating, just until well mixed.
Stir in nuts. Cover; chill dough for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Let stay on cookie sheet 2 to 3 minutes before removing to wire racks.
Roll in remaining confectioners sugar. Cool completely, then roll again in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk and ham chunks in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix together Bisquick and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes before serving.

title: easy cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
To prepare crust, in medium saucepan place 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Heat until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and press mixture evenly over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: carrot and cheese casserole
directions: Drain carrots and put in casserole.
Heat 1 stick butter and cheese in microwave until melted.
Pour cheese mixture over carrots.
Stir croutons together with 1/2 stick melted butter. Pour on top of carrots.
Cook, uncovered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: harvest nut pie
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Put pie crust in pie dish.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Cover with second pie crust.
Poke holes or cut middle for steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream together brown sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Stir in pumpkin and milk.
Mix thoroughly flour, baking powder, salt, ginger, soda and cloves.
Stir in pumpkin mixture.
Beat for 1 minute with electric mixer.
Add nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool. Wrap and store overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Sift together the flour and baking soda, set aside.
In a large bowl, cream together the butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Stir in the instant pudding until blended.
Then stir in the eggs and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Finally, stir in the chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop cookies by rounded spoonfuls onto unprepared cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in the preheated oven. Edges should be golden brown.

title: drew's salsa
directions: Mix it all up in your Salsa Master or dice it all up by hand.

title: eagle brand cherry cheese pie
directions: In
a
large
bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in	Eagle Brand until smooth. Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling, then serve.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Drain 1/2 gallon dill pickles.
Cut in fourths.
Re-pack in jar.
Boil together 2 1/2 cups sugar and 1 cup vinegar.
Drain and reheat.
Pour over pickles and refrigerate.
Makes one half gallon. Good and cheaper than boughten sweet pickles.

title: party stuffed bell peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cut peppers in half through stem. Remove and discard seeds. Place peppers in a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan, cut side up. In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well. Use a scoop to equally divide beef mixture into inside of bell peppers. Press gently to fill all of inside. Heap on top if necessary. Pour 1 quart of prepared spaghetti sauce over tops and bake 30 minutes or until beef is cooked. Makes 12 servings.

title: ultimate pancakes
directions: Stir ingredients until blended.
Pour by scant 1/4 cupfuls onto hot griddle. Cook until edges are dry. Turn; cook until golden. Makes 12 or 13
pancakes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown together meat, seasoned with Tony Chacheres seasoning, onion, pepper and celery.
Drain fat.
Put in casserole dish. Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check the last half hour to see if rice is cooked.
If dry, add 1/2 cup of water and stir.
May add more cheese to top, if desired.

title: aunt terry's cherry bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on cooled pastry.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting and drop of red food coloring.

title: german kaffee kuchen
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Take out 3/4 cup of this and add the cinnamon and nuts to the rest of the mixture.
Add the last 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain 1/2 liquid off beets.
Heat with onion until soft. Separately, mix together sugar, salt, cornstarch and vinegar.
Add to hot beets and onion slowly.
Stir as mixture thickens.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Arrange ladyfingers in glass dish.
Whip cream until quite firm.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until soft.
Fold into whipped cream.
Spoon evenly on ladyfingers.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: cheese scones
directions: Sift together flour, salt and mustard.
Rub in butter until mixture feels like bread crumbs.
Finely grate cheese and add 3 1/2 ounces to the flour mixture.

title: cream of green chili soup(serves 6)
directions: Heat butter; add flour and cook low heat for 2 minutes.
Cool. In separate pan bring stock to boil; add chilies that have gone through food processor.
Add cilantro, salt, pepper and cumin. Add to chicken soup.
To break up lumps, whip while adding the cream.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Drain and flake salmon, discarding bone and skin.
Beat eggs. Grate onion.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons into hot fat; cook until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: french-fried onion rings
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Add milk, oil and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Peel and slice onions into 1/4-inch rings. Separate into rings.
Dip each into batter and drop a few at a time into hot oil.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes, turning a few at a time. Drain on paper towels.
Best fried in iron frying pan in 1 inch of oil.

title: honey-glazed chicken breasts
directions: Arrange sliced almonds in shallow baking pan.
Broil 1 minute, stirring often, until golden brown.
In 6-quart kettle combine onion, celery, carrot, parsley, salt, pepper, rosemary, bay leaf, undiluted chicken breasts and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove kettle from heat and chill chicken mixture overnight.

title: refrigerator angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine in a bowl, flour, salt, baking powder, soda and sugar.
Cut in shortening, buttermilk and yeast water to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in half gallon container in refrigerator.
Use as needed for hot rolls.
Bake at 400°.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread drained sauerkraut in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Arrange tomatoes over sauerkraut; spread with dressing and dot with margarine.
Top with corned beef and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus chocolate chip cookie recipe
directions: Cream the butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda. Add chips, candy and nuts. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.
Recipe can be halved.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Cook rice.
Add to remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Slice pound cake in half, lengthwise.
Mix topping and pudding, then add drained pineapple and liqueur or juice and extract.
Spread between layers and frost with this mixture. Garnish with sliced almonds.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool and remove from pan.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Simmer on low until candy melts.
Great for holidays.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute bacon and add onion, celery, garlic and basil.
Stir in soup.
Bring to boil; heat 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and zucchini. Cook 10 minutes.
Makes 8 cups.

title: poke cake
directions: Bake white cake mix in a sheet cake pan according to package directions.
Cool cake; leave in pan and poke holes all over it with a cooking fork.
Prepare jello with 1 cup hot water; pour over the cake.
Refrigerate.

title: peaches and cream salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water. Stir in the cold water. Add pie filling. Chill slightly.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook ground chuck until brown, breaking into chunks (not crumbly).
Drain any fat.
In Dutch oven, add meat, water, bouillon and onion.
Bring to boil.
Add vegetables.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel; cut into 1/2-inch cubes and boil
eggplant
until done. Drain and stir in egg, onion and crackers
to
thicken. Pour layers of eggplant and mushroom soup into
casserole
and top with
grated
cheese.
Cook
in 350° oven for 15
to
20 minutes.

title: 5 pounds chocolate fudge
directions: In large heavy pan, combine sugar, milk, butter and vanilla; bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly for exactly 11 minutes.
Turn burner off, add marshmallows, nuts and chocolate chips.
Beat until marshmallows and chocolate chips are dissolved and mixture is smooth.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add drained pineapple and blueberries.
Let gel until firm. Mix remaining ingredients and spread over jello.
Top with chopped nuts or crushed cookies.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan, except vanilla and nuts. Cook, stirring constantly, until soft ball or 234° is reached. Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered dish and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in large skillet.
Drain and reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender, but not brown.
Stir in beans, bacon and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in oil.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots, nuts and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into a floured and greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together. Pour into a well-greased and floured pie tin. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until sharp knife comes out clean. Pie forms its own crust.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Add bouillon cubes and soup. Pour into slow cooker, add cheese.
Stir occasionally as cheese is melting.
Makes approximately 1/2 gallon.

title: lemon sunshine cake
directions: Mix together. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Easy Method.
Break eggs in blender container and stir.
Add bananas, margarine and sugar.
Stir in flour, soda, vanilla and salt until blended.
Add nuts after you turn the blender off.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Cut the eggplant in slices, sprinkle with a little salt and deep fry in oil. Put the fried egg plant into a dish and mix the rest of the ingredients.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Then egg.
Add salt and vanilla.
Sift cocoa and flour together and add to other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turkey grape salad
directions: Combine mayo, lemon juice, basil, salt and pepper in bowl and blend well.
Add turkey to taste, celery and grapes.
Mix lightly. Chill.
Serve on lettuce; garnish with whole grapes and apple slices.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Drain vegetables.
Add to cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread bread lightly with mayo or soft butter before filling sandwiches. This helps to prevent sogginess.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together the shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg, bananas and sour milk.
Sift and add to mixture the flour, soda, powder and salt.
Add the nuts.

title: clam sauce
directions: Brown garlic in olive oil. Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes. Pour over linguine or your favorite pasta.

title: dipped pretzels(club member: john waters)
directions: Melt almond bark. Dip pretzels one at a time. Lay on wax paper to cool.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together. Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix powdered sugar, 3 eggs, vanilla and cream cheese together; pour over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy apple pie
directions: Mix all - pour over apples in pie plate.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Make a soft crust.
Sprinkle with additional cinnamon and sugar.

title: oyster-corn bread dressing
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in enough broth to make mixture moist and very wet.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch or a 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: stollen
directions: Combine 2 cups bread flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Heat milk, water and butter to 120° to 130°.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs.
Blend at low speed; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in cherries, citron, raisins, walnuts and remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise until doubled.
Punch down; divide in half.
Pat each to 14 x 8-inch oval.
Fold in half lengthwise.
Curve into a crescent.
Press edges to seal. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover; let rise until doubled. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drizzle with a glaze; garnish with cherries and nuts.
Makes 2 small Stollen.

title: chocolate velvet cake frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Slowly stir in boiling water until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly,	until mixture
thickens.	Add chocolate and butter; stir until
melted. Remove
from
heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a bowl
and
chill, stirring
often, until it becomes spreading consistency.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in a large plastic bag, using a rolling pin. Cream together the butter, cheese and sugar.
In another bowl, cream together the milk, pudding mix and whipped topping.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Mix well.
Fill clean flowerpot, ceramic pot or 13 x 9-inch dish with alternate layers of crumbs and pudding mixture, beginning and ending with crumbs.
Freeze or refrigerate.
Place a few gummy worms on top before serving and place plastic flowers in the middle.
Great for Christmas parties.

title: turkey gravy
directions: In roasting pan, mix turkey drippings and all-purpose flour. Gradually add Swanson clear chicken broth.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Makes 2 cups.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and pretzels.
Mix well and put into a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water; while hot add to chilled strawberries.
Cool until mixture begins to set.
Meanwhile, cream sugar and cream cheese mixture.
Spread over cooled crust.
When gelatin begins to set, pour over mixture. Enjoy!

title: jello salad #1
directions: You will need a 9 x 13 glass dish.

title: pasta with sun-dried tomatoes and garlic
directions: Bring pasta later to boil.
In a medium nonstick skillet, saute garlic 1 to 2 minutes in olive oil and sun-dried tomatoes.
Pour cooked pasta into skillet; add garlic and sun-dried tomatoes, black pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Toss to combine.
Serve immediately on warm plate.
Add extra cheese.

title: apple walnut ring cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and mace.
Add to batter gradually. Stir in vanilla, apples and nuts.
Batter will be thick. Spoon into greased and floured 12-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old-fashioned brownies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa and salt in bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl with a whisk, combine butter and coffee powder.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Add sugar, whisking to blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in nuts.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Tie spices loosely in bag and bring to boiling in water.
Add tea tied loosely in bag; steep 5 minutes.
Remove bags.
Heat fruit juices and sugar; add to tea.
Serves 25.

title: honey drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in honey and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix again well.
Chill.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Form in balls and pat down.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook garlic, beef and oregano until meat is dry.
Cook onion, salad oil and chili powder until limp.
Add to meat.
Add tomato sauce, paste, water, beans, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Put Fritos in bottom of dish.
Cover with mixture and put cheese on top. Bake.

title: potato slices with sour cream and mock caviar
directions: Scrub the potatoes and boil in salt water until they can easily be pricked with a fork.
Drain. Cut into small slices and place in serving dish.
Pour over the sour cream and then the olives. Serve immediately.
Serves 5.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add pineapple and blueberry pie filling mix.
Pour half in 9 x 13-inch pan; let set.
Mix the other with sour cream, mayo, vanilla and sugar.
Pour on top of the rest and chill.

title: spanish rice
directions: Wash uncooked rice.
Brown meat and add ingredients.
Turn to low heat for 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian ham and rice casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine honey, margarine, mustard, soy sauce and green pepper.
Mix well; add remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly and turn into a greased casserole.
Bake covered for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Leftovers good cold.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in a medium saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in cocoa, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well. Working quickly, drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together milk, egg and oil.
Add milk mixture to cornmeal mixture.
Stir only enough to mix.
Fill greased baking pan 1/2 full.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground round and onion together in Dutch oven size pan. Add all other ingredients and bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for about five minutes.
You can also add 1/4 c. of Minute Rice if desired.

title: linguini salad
directions: Also, you may add cherry tomatoes, scallions, celery or a can of peas (drained) and salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Fold in flour, milk, baking powder, salt and zest of 1 lemon. Spray 1 medium loaf pan with Pam. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Cool loaf.

title: chip 'n nut bars
directions: Put all ingredients except nuts and chips together.
Mix on lowest speed of mixer or by hand until well blended.
Add 1/2 package chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread in a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan that has been coated with margarine.
Top with remaining 1/2 package chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares before serving.

title: lemon apple salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup juice.
Let set in an 8x8-inch pan to quiver stage.
Add fruit and nuts.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the grated cheese over top.
Refrigerate.
Make topping: beat egg slightly; add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 Tbsp. flour.
Stir; add 1/2 cup juice.
Cook while stirring.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, Blue cheese and butter.
Fold in other ingredients except the nuts.
Form into a ball and chill at least 4 hours.
Roll balls in nuts and serve with crackers.

title: white velvet cut-outs
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese, preferably with a mixer. Add sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat until well-mixed. gradually incorporate flour and mix well.
Cover well and chill several hours or overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash the broccoli and cut the tips off.
The tips will be used for the salad.
Cover the tips with sliced onion, raisins and bacon bits.
Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar for the dressing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken at 350° until done; season to taste.
Boil potatoes until tender and drain.
Place potatoes over chicken breasts.
Slice Velveeta cheese over potatoes.
Place in oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oven dish meal
directions: Mix all together or put in baking dish in order given. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Baking dish should be greased and deep.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: snack pizzas
directions: Pat each biscuit round into a 4-inch circle on baking sheet. Mix tomato paste and oregano.
Brush on each biscuit round.
Mix onion and mushrooms.
Sprinkle over tomato paste mixture and top with shredded cheese.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake until crust is lightly browned, about 8 minutes, in a 400° oven.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Boil raisins, dates, pineapple and water for 3 minutes.
Add oleo and cool.
Then add flour, Sweet 'N Low, nuts, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Season chicken thighs with salt and pepper.
Dip in egg and roll in cracker crumbs.
Saute until golden in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add remaining butter as you turn pieces over; saute until golden on second side.
Combine onion soup and water; pour over chicken.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until chicken is cooked, about 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: country style steak
directions: Put chopped onion into large sauce pot and add approximately 3 C water. Bring to boil and lower heat. Salt, pepper and flour steak and fry in hot oil. Put steak in pot of water and onions.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 2 cups cornflakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a medium size mixing bowl, then add raisins.
Add vinegar to the milk and stir into the dry ingredients, mixing well (the dough is sticky).
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently for about 1 minute.
Grease and flour bunny mold or spray with nonstick cooking spray like Pam and lightly flour.
Place dough in mold, making sure to fill mold evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool Raisin Bread Bunny completely on wire rack, then have fun decorating as desired with thin icing topped with flaked coconut or topping of your choice.

title: peach cake
directions: Cook cake in 9 x 13 glass pan.
Cool cake.
Poke holes in cake and pour juice only from peaches over cake.
Add peach slices next (save several for top of cake).
Mix together Cool Whip and pudding, then pour over cake.
Add the peach slices.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and sugar together.
Add oleo.
Pat mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely. Then mix powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Add Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries or raspberries.
Pour over ingredients in pan. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini rich buns
directions: *Zucchini Milk:
In blender or food processor, puree 2 to 3 peeled zucchini until smooth.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and onion.
Blend well. Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Top with cherry.

title: apple dumplins'
directions: Separate crescent rolls and wrap around a wedge of peeled Granny Smith apple. Place in buttered baking dish. Continue until all crescent rolls are used. Sprinkle sugar mixture over the rolls. Pour melted butter over rolls and then the 12 ounces of Mountain Dew. Bake at 250° for approximately 30 minutes. Check for brownness and texture of apple. Very good with whipped cream or a scoop of vanilla bean ice cream.

title: rhubarb sauce
directions: Add water to rhubarb and cook rhubarb until soft; cool.
Add liquid artificial sweetener.
A dash of nutmeg may be added after cooking if desired.
Yield: 4 servings.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 1 g, fat 0 g, calories 32.
One serving = 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: cho-nut pie
directions: Stir together the first 3 ingredients.
Stir well all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: savory spaghetti
directions: Brown meat in large skillet over medium heat. Add onion, green pepper and cook 5 min. Add olives, mushrooms, tomato sauce, and mix lightly. Stir mixture of tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, worcestershire sauce, tabasco, into meat mixture. Add uncooked spaghetti and bring to a boil. Cover tightly, reduce heat to low and simmer about 40 min. stirring occasionally. Uncover and simmer 15 min. longer. About 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 11/2 sticks margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake about 5 minutes in 350° oven in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Beat eggs, remaining margarine and confectioners sugar about 15 minutes.
Spread over cooled crust.
Add pineapple in even layer over sugar mixture.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Spoon on Cool Whip.
Cover with nuts and cherries.
If using sliced strawberries, omit cherries.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours or overnight.
Serves about 16.

title: instant miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture. Mix well.
Place desired amount of dough on floured cloth, pat out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rolls come to room temperature before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: aroma of christmas
directions: Combine spices and fruit with water in sauce pan or crockpot. Bring to a boil and simmer.
Check hourly; add water as needed.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute the celery, onion and mushrooms in butter.
In saucepan, place sauteed ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for approximately 15 minutes.
In individual bowls, place Fritos, grated Cheddar cheese and desired amount of picante sauce.
Pour hot soup over this and serve.
This is very fast to make and is delicious.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add the rest and blend by hand, only until moist and well blended.
Bake in ungreased loaf pan for 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine the sour cream, soup, and poppy seeds.
Stir in chicken.
Pour into a greased 11 in. x 7 in. x 2 in. baking dish. Combine the cracker crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°F for 25 - 30 min. or until heated through.

title: cheeseburger buns
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, shortening, egg, salt, and 2 c. flour; beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 4-6 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.
In a skillet, cook beef and onion until beef is no longer pink.
Set aside.
Stir tomato sauce and remove from head. Divide dough into 16 pieces on a lightly floured surface.
Roll out and stretch each piece.
Top each piece with cheese and 3 Tbsp. beef, bring dough over and seal.
Let rise and bake at 400 degrees for 20-30 minutes.

title: cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Butter bottom of Bundt pan.
Pour nuts around bottom of pan. Arrange one row of frozen rolls around bottom of pan.
In a two cup measuring cup, place pudding, cinnamon and add brown sugar to 1 cup line.
Mix together.
Pour mixture over rolls.
Pour melted butter over rolls.
Cover pan with a tea towel and put in cool place overnight (to rise).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Flip out of pan onto a plate and scoop what is left in pan over rolls.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until spins thread.
Add pecans. Stir continually until syrup turns golden brown.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Stir until butter melts.
Pour quickly on 2 cookie sheets with sides.
As mixture begins to harden around the edges, pull until thin.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour melted oleo into bottom of baking dish.
Mix together the sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into melted oleo (don't stir).
Pour peaches on top of mixture (don't stir).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan, cook onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Crumble sausage into pan, stirring with a fork to break it into smaller pieces.
Chop and remove the seeds from the green pepper and add it; cook until meat is well browned.
Dice tomatoes and add them with their juice to the pan.
Add broth, oregano, zucchini, parsley and vinegar.
Bring to a boil over high heat. When boiling, add pasta and cook, uncovered, until pasta and squash are tender.

title: appetizer salad
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 14 to 19 minutes.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Spread on roll crusts.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Garnish with vegetables.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers well.
Soak in cold water overnight.
Next day, pack in hot, sterilized jars.
To each quart, add the given amount of alum, garlic, red pepper and dill.
Combine vinegar, salt and water; bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.
Let rest several weeks.
Place in refrigerator to crisp.

title: melt in your mouth blueberry cake
directions: Grease and flour an 8-inch square pan.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine nuts, sugar, syrup and salt in glass bowl and microwave 4 minutes.
Stir and replace for 3 minutes.
Add margarine; stir and heat 2 minutes.
Remove and add soda and vanilla.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet until hard and cool. Break into pieces.

title: italian country chicken
directions: Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic, broccoli and carrots.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and stir until cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Mix in artichoke hearts with liquid, peppers with liquid and olives.
Heat through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over pasta and toss well.
Serve with Parmesan cheese for sprinkling. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together and drain.
Mix corn meal, eggs, sweet milk, and corn.
Grease 12-inch cast iron skillet with bacon drippings and heat in 350° oven until hot.
Pour hot grease into corn bread mixture, then pour 1/2 of batter in skillet. Sprinkle browned beef and onion and grated cheese evenly over batter in skillet.
Pour rest of batter over the meat and cheese. Bake for 50 minutes.
(Good with green salad or pinto beans.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix all together.
Roll out into little balls and place on cookie sheet.
Mash with fork.
Bake until brown in oven at 350°.

title: layered twenty-four hour salad
directions: In a very large salad bowl, line the bottom with bite size pieces of lettuce.
Cover the lettuce with carrots, celery, onions, water chestnuts and peas.
Spread the quart of mayonnaise on top as if you are icing a cake.
Sprinkle Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses on top.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Serves 16.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon into deep fryer (360° to 370°) for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Put
butter
in
milk and bring to boil.
In a bowl mix eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk and butter mixture and mix
well. Let this all cool.
Add baking powder and vanilla. Mix all ingredients together well.	Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat
eggs
at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar and lemon juice.
Stir in pumpkin.	Sift together flour, baking soda,
cinnamon
and
salt.
Add
to
pumpkin mixture. Spread on a
greased	and
floured
jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Sprinkle
the
nuts
on
top of the batter.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Place a dish towel on top and turn cake out, then starting at the narrow end, roll towel and cake together. Cool
and unroll.
Spread
filling over cake.
Roll again and chill.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool and take off bones.
Add onions and rice to broth.
Cook until tender.
Mix soup and yogurt and add half to rice.
Cook broccoli until tender.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 7 ingredients.
Mix together the 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Roll the first mixture into small balls, like walnuts.
Roll into mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until brown, but still soft, at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Pour oyster crackers in a large bowl.
Add the package of dry Ranch dressing.
Pour the whole bottle of oil over the crackers and dressing.
Mix very well. Eat!

title: starlight punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Pour into 5-quart freezer container.
Cover tightly and freeze (up to 1 month).

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Let stand about 20 minutes.
Peel and thinly slice cucumbers; add and mix well. Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 6.

title: freezer sweet corn
directions: Boil 1 to 5 minutes, then cool. Freeze.

title: cherry pie no. 2
directions: Mix
Cool Whip, lemon juice and condensed milk.
Divide into crusts.
Put
pie
filling
on top (equally between the 2 pies). Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Steam together the broccoli and the onion for a few minutes. Then cool.
Mix all together and bake in pan of your choice for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Pop popcorn without butter or oil.
It needs to be dry.
Mix together margarine, corn syrup, brown sugar and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in baking soda, stirring well.
This will foam up.
Pour over popcorn and mix well. Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper and store in airtight container.
Yields 15 servings.
Preparation time is 75 minutes.

title: old fashion caramel pie
directions: In heavy skillet, add sugar, flour and salt.
Place on heat and heat without stirring until 3 to 4 small puffs of smoke rise out of mixture.
Have milk ready to pour in at that moment and stir, stirring frequently.
The sugar, flour mixture hardens, but will dissolve with slow heat and stirring, cook and stir until crystals melt and is thickened.
Beat egg yolks until creamy. Lift out several spoonfuls of caramel.
Mix with egg yolks.
Add egg yolk.
Mix to caramel in skillet.
Add butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.

title: easy christmas cookies
directions: Mix cake, eggs and oil until well blended. Chill about 1 hour. Take out.
Flour countertop or table. Roll out and cut out with cookie cutters. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool and decorate to taste.

title: spaghetti torta
directions: Butter spring-form pan.
Coat with Parmesan cheese. Cook spaghetti. Rinse and drain. Fry sausage, ground beef and onion; drain and add mushrooms.

title: campers pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and sugar and put in a 9-inch pie pan.
In a 2-cup measuring cup, measure oil.
Blend in milk; stir until milky.
Then pour into first mixture.
Start patting in center, working dough out to the edge.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
May be filled with fruit before baking or used for other fillings.

title: fruit trifle
directions: In 2 1/2 or 3-quart glass bowl, layer 1/3 of cake cubes, then 1/3 pudding.
Mix fruit and jam and place 1/3 on top of pudding. Repeat layers.
Top with frozen whipped topping.
Use a few pieces of fruit for decoration.

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute or until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies and Cocoa Puffs.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper sprayed with Pam.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift flour with soda.
Stir in order given.
No need to use mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: raspberry mousse pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and stir constantly until berries separate and gelatin begins to thicken.
Blend in whipped topping, then whip until smooth.
Chill until mixture mounds.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours. Garnish with additional whipped topping and raspberries.

title: holiday spread
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine Wispride, cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Stir in olives, green pepper, bacon and chilies.
Spoon into serving bowl; refrigerate.
Serve with Old London rounds.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: bev's 24-hour coleslaw
directions: Stir sugar into cabbage.
Put half of the cabbage into a large bowl.
Cover with onion slices; top with remaining cabbage.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all except broccoli together.
Mix with broccoli; top with Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Saute onion, then brown ground beef in skillet.
Add tomato soup, water, green beans and noodles.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up raw cabbage and fill a 3-quart baking dish about 3/4 full.
Saute bacon, onions and pepper.
Add tomato sauce, corn, chili powder and catsup.
Simmer a few minutes.
Pour over cabbage and bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Stir and bake another 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine ingredients for teriyaki sauce and pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight.
Bake approximately 1 hour in 325° oven, turning every 15 minutes. Serves approximately 6 people.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip and spread in bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup of milk in bowl.
Add pudding; beat with whisk until well blended.
Mixture will be very thick.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly in a large mixer bowl. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend on low speed about 30 seconds. Mix on medium speed until ingredients are well blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls (heaping) onto greased cookie sheet. Bake about 12 minutes.
Frost, if desired.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: scallop and corn chowder(makes about 4 cups)
directions: Saute the bacon in a large saucepan until crisp.
Set aside to drain on paper towels.
Discard all but 1/2 teaspoon of bacon fat left in pan.
Add onion or leek.
Saute over low heat, stirring until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add the potatoes and chicken broth and heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and pecans together.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Mix first 6 ingredients and pour 1/3 of batter in pan. Sprinkle sugar mixture (1/3) over batter.
Repeat 2 more times. Bake 60 to 65 minutes in a 300° to 325° oven.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken nugget casserole
directions: Place chicken nuggets in greased 11 x 7 baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Top with spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Italian seasoning. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is heated through and cheese is melted. YIELD: 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine vegetables, eggs and salt.
Put in large casserole. Combine crushed saltines and margarine.
Put on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Soak raisins in boiling water until soft.
Drain.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix well. Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add gradually to pumpkin mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Combine oleo, powdered sugar, maple flavoring and milk.
Ice cookies while they are warm.

title: applesauce 7-up salad
directions: Heat the applesauce and dissolve the jello in it.
Add the pineapple, including juice, let cool and add 7-Up and nuts.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Sweet and Sour Salad: Remove seasoning packet from Ramen noodles and reserve for another use. Melt butter in olive oil over medium heat. Add noodles broken into pieces, and walnuts or pecans. Saute until lightly browned. Drain on paper towels. Toss together noodle mixture, spinach, lettuce and green onions in a large bowl.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: fudge marble brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/4 cup water, eggs and oleo in large bowl; beat at low speed with electric mixer until just blended.
Measure 1/2 cup batter into small bowl.
Add cocoa packet, chocolate chips and 1 tablespoon water.
Stir until blended.
Add nuts to yellow batter.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon chocolate batter randomly on top.
Swirl with knife (like marble cake). Bake at 350° for 22 to 27 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 32 (2 x 1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients
to
make
a batter; stir well. Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix
until blended.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: layered green salad
directions: Layer items in order in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and chill; before serving, sprinkle with 3 hard-boiled eggs, chopped. Crumble bacon (or mushrooms or sunflower seeds) and tomato wedges. Serves 6 to 10.

title: frozen date salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin cups and freeze.
Allow to soften before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: no name soup
directions: Mix soup and milk in saucepan over medium heat.
Cut dogs into bite-size pieces.
Add to soup.
Add macaroni.
When hot, serve.

title: jellied guacamole salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve in boiling water.
Pour a little clear gelatin in bottom of mold; arrange shrimp in it and chill until firm (shrimp may be marinated in French dressing for a few hours beforehand; then drain well).
Mash avocado with lemon juice; add seasonings and remaining gelatin.
Pour mixture on top of firm shrimp layer.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving dish. Garnish with lettuce, tomato and cucumber wedges.
Serve with mayonnaise.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on a lightly greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: cavolfiore - fritti(cauliflower fritters)
directions: Boil cauliflower until tender, not too soft.
Break into small pieces.
Mix pancake flour and water.
Dip cauliflower into batter.
Fry in frying pan or deep fryer until golden brown. Serves many.

title: microwave seasoned potatoes
directions: Mix butter, pepper and seasoned salt and pour over potatoes in microwave bowl.
Cover.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir and continue to cook for 10 to 15 minutes until done.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Add 1/3 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Blend gradually.
Add the 1 1/4 cups milk and 1 1/4 cups chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick. Add 4 ounce can of drained mushrooms.

title: pineapple orange cake
directions: Combine and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: derek's favorite waldorf salad
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with whipping cream and powdered sugar.
Add mayonnaise and then mix in the remaining ingredients, adding the Cool Whip last.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy chicken bake
directions: Pour rice in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix in soup.
Lay pieces of chicken on top.
Sprinkle top soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake.
(I put this in at 9:00 a.m. at 250° and it is done when we get home from church at about 12:30 p.m.)

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; add onion.
Add all dry ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomato paste and juice.
Simmer 1 hour (3 or more hours is better).
Can be thinned with water.

title: the very best banana pudding
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with wafers or cookies and then layer sliced bananas on top. In a large bowl, combine milk and pudding. Blend well, using an electric mixer. Using a medium bowl, combine cream cheese and condensed milk together and mix until smooth. Fold the Cool Whip into the cream cheese mixture. Add the cream cheese mixture to the pudding mixture and stir until blended. Pour mixture over bananas and cover with remaining wafers or cookies. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rocky road
directions: Place chocolate morsels, milk and butter in top of double boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate and butter melt, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanuts and marshmallows.
Place mixture into a wax paper lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: topping for angel food cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add
sugar,
juice
and rind from lemon and orange.
Cook until
thick.
Cool.	Add
pint	cream (whipped) or Cool Whip can be used instead of cream.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots on the bias in 1-inch chunks.
Cook, covered, in boiling salted water until just tender, about 20 minutes; drain. In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, ginger and salt.
Add juice; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in butter.
Toss with carrots.
Serves 4.

title: mock devonshire cream
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, and salt; stir until well blended. Stir in whipping cream. With an electric mixer, beat until stiff.

title: quick glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrot into match sticks and place in cold water.
When ready to cook, drain water from carrot and place them in a frypan along with butter, salt, pepper and sugar.
Steam cook until just tender; check seasoning and add more if needed.

title: rena's chinese chicken casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, salt and soup for dressing.
Toss all together and sprinkle on top the butter, slivered almonds and corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Don't let the corn flakes scare you.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch dish with slices of cake.
Mix jello with 2 cups hot water and juice from pineapple; pour over cake.
Mix pudding according to package and pour over jello.
Spread crushed pineapple and Cool Whip; sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: minted sundae soda
directions: Combine jelly and water in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until jelly dissolves.
Cool, then chill.
Into tall chilled glasses, pour about 3 tablespoons mint jelly syrup.
Add spoonful of sherbet or ice cream; stir until melted.
Add a scoop of vanilla ice cream, then scoop of lime sherbet.
Finish with another scoop of vanilla.
Fill glass with lemon-lime carbonated beverage; pour carefully down side of glass to save sparkle (bubbles).
Garnish with lime slices and mint sprig.
(May use 2 teaspoons creme de menthe syrup in each glass in place of mint jelly syrup.

title: nick's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Meanwhile, in another pan, melt margarine. Blend in flour; add milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Season.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Divide macaroni between 2 greased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Pour sauce over. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
(Can freeze before baking.)

title: crunchy top sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup butter, eggs and milk in	bowl; mix well.
Spoon	into
baking
dish.
Combine brown sugar,
cup
butter, flour and pecans in bowl; mix well. Sprinkle
over
casserole.	Bake at 350° for 3 minutes. Yield:
8 servings.

title: caviar spread
directions: Chop eggs and mix with mayonnaise.
Spread mixture in a well-greased 8-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle onions over egg mixture.
Soften cream cheese and blend with sour cream until smooth.
Spread this mixture over onions with a wet spatula.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.
Top creatively with caviar.
Serve with crackers or toast points.

title: wiener bun sandwiches
directions: Break up all of the ingredients.
Add just enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Put mixture on wiener buns and wrap in foil. Heat in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 18 to 20 sandwiches.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together and let stand 1 hour.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Beat eggs and then add oil and vanilla.
Blend apple mixture with egg mixture. Add flour mixture to egg and apple mixture.
Stir in coconut, walnuts and cherries.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan.
After cake has cooled, remove from pan and top with confectioners sugar.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut lettuce, onion and cauliflower into a large container. Add bacon.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise together and pour over all ingredients.
Add cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Let set overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: haupia
directions: Make a smooth paste of the dry ingredients and 1/2 c. of coconut milk. Add remaining coconut milk and cook on low heat, stirring rapidly. Cook until clear and thick enough to coat a spoon. To avoid curdling, be sure to use low heat. Pour into a shallow pan and set in a cool place until firm.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Wash mushrooms lightly and quickly put through a grinder. Saute for 2 minutes in butter.
Dredge over with flour.
Add milk, stirring until smooth.
Simmer until it thickens and serve.

title: wormy apples
directions: Cut apple into 3 cross sections (your choice to core or not). Spread 1 teaspoon Cool Whip in between layers.
Stack back together and skewer to hold.
Put small hole in apple and place gummy worm in leaving part hanging out.
Serves 1.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften cheese and butter. Mix with all ingredients.
Spread on muffin halves and then cut in quarters.
Can quick freeze on a tray and then put in Baggies for freezer.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
If taking too long to brown, put under broiler.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix eggs with syrup, salt, vanilla, sugar and butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Measure flour and oatmeal and then blend.
Put small amounts in blender until it turns to powder.
Mix together.
Mix all ingredients and add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line baking dish with tinfoil.
In 1 bowl, melt butter in microwave until liquid.
In larger bowl, mix chips, parsley and cheese.
Dip chicken into butter, then into chip mixture.
Place into pan.
Pour remaining butter into pan and pack remaining chip mixture on top of chicken.
Bake covered until chicken is done.
Uncover and return to oven until crispy and golden brown.

title: chocolate mousse(serves 12 or more)
directions: Cut chocolate into 1/2 inch pieces and place in a saucepan. Place pan in almost boiling water and cover.
Let chocolate melt over lowered heat.
Put yolks in a heavy saucepan and add the 3 tablespoons water.
Place saucepan over very low heat while beating vigorously and constantly with a wire whisk, being careful not to burn.
When yolks start to thicken, add Amaretto.
Continue beating until sauce is consistency of a Hollandaise sauce.
Remove from heat.

title: boiled filet of sole
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Squeeze into the pan the juice of 1/2 lemon; take out seeds.
Add mayonnaise and dry vermouth and stir with a fork.
Lay out filets on foil on a broiler pan.
Pour and spread evenly the mixture from the saucepan over the filets. Let sit for 15 minutes or so.
Sprinkle with a little paprika and broil close to flame.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Gradually add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Combine parsley, onion, chicken, lemon juice, sage, salt and pepper; add to white sauce.
Chill.
Shape into 8 croquettes.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken wings; pat dry.
In a bowl, combine the crumbled crackers or bread crumbs, herbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add seasonings and mix well to blend.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken wings, first into melted butter, then into crumb coating.
Arrange chicken wings in lightly oiled ovenproof baking dish.
Bake chicken wings at 375°
for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Chicken wings should be tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add to sauce.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place small amount of sauce.
Lay 3 strips of uncooked lasagne lengthwise.
Spread with 1/3 spaghetti sauce, 1/3 cottage cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat layers process twice. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off paper; cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix sour cream, soup, milk, melted butter and onion together and pour over potatoes.
Add cheese on top and cover with Rice Krispies.
Place sliced butter on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onions and pepper in 2 tablespoon of oil, about 5 minutes.
Mash tomatoes.
Add all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.

title: butterscotch cheesecake
directions: Melt morsels and butter and stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy and add other ingredients and pour over cream mixture.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bote koek (sheet cookies)
directions: Cream butter or oleo, add all other ingredients except almonds and reserved egg white. Spread into a greased sheet cake pan. Sprinkle slivered almonds on top. Beat reserved egg white and spread over top. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until done.

title: hot peanut butter fudge sauce
directions: Cook first five ingredients 3 minutes until thick, then add vanilla.
Take from stove and stir in peanut butter.
This will thicken as it cools.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs. Add baby food. Mix together flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, sugar and nuts. Add to previous mixture. Bake in greased and floured pan at 325°, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ragout of rabbit
directions: Place rabbit in kettle with onions, bay leaves, celery, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer, covered, 2 hours or until rabbit is nearly tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and mushrooms (sliced). Simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until all is tender.
Blend flour with water.
Stir into stew.
Cook until thickened.
Add parsley and Tabasco.
Serves 6.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in a large bowl on High until chocolate and margarine are melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate mixture.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well-blended.
Stir in flour and nuts.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter; add peanut butter and sugar.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate bark and dip.

title: mexicana quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tortillas, in bowl; mix. Layer, starting with tortillas in a 9-inch pie pan or quiche dish, then spread some mixture on tortilla.
Repeat, tortilla, then mixture, ending with tortilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: doves with orange glaze
directions: Spread quail open; pat dry with paper towels.
Combine 1/4 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Dredge quail in flour mixture. Heat 1/4-inch of oil in a skillet; place quail in skillet and brown on both sides, turning once.
Remove from skillet.
Combine 3 tablespoons flour, 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt; stir until smooth.
Blend into drippings in skillet.
Place quail in gravy and add enough water to half cover birds.
Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve birds, breast side up, over hot cooked rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fig upside-down cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar, fig preserves and water.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Then mix together eggs, sugar, margarine, milk, vanilla and flour.
Pour over fig mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Turn over in cake plate.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours. Serve as a dip with tortilla chips, or as a mild sauce for other dishes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into very small pieces.
Dice onions and slice carrots very thin.
Mix all together.

title: grama's cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and rest of ingredients; mix well.
Chill in fridge one hour.
Spoon on cookie sheet, allow room to spread and bake for 12 (approximately) minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hawaiian loin of pork
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With paring knife, make several small slits at intervals on pork.
Insert in slits half of the ginger. Combine rest of ginger and soy sauce; brush fat side of pork with part of mixture.
Brush several times during roasting.
Roast without a rack for 1 hour and 45 minutes, or until meat thermometer reads 185°.
Remove from oven; wait 20 minutes before carving.
Garnish with watercress and bananas, baked in orange juice.

title: squash dressing
directions: Bake at 375° until brown, not dry.

title: danish pastries
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk, beaten eggs and yeast (which has been dissolved in lukewarm water and vanilla).
After ingredients are thoroughly mixed, divide dough into small balls. (If dough is too sticky to work with, add flour to right consistency.)
Layer into bowl with wax paper between layers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients until like, but not as thick as, pie crust.
Measure egg and if it isn't 1/4 cup, fill on up with water to equal 1/4 cup.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix.
Roll out to make cookies or drop by teaspoon and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Beat by hand or mixer 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: judy's easy cake
directions: Mix.
Bake as directed on cake box.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In
medium saucepan, melt margarine. Stir in flour and
salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture coats
spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Stir until melted.
Stir in cooked macaroni.

title: refreshing orange dip
directions: Place cream cheese and concentrate in blender or food processor container; cover.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate. Serve with assorted fruit dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: vicki's easy brownies
directions: Combine sugar and eggs in bowl.
Melt chocolate and butter separately.
Add to sugar and eggs. Add flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and oleo;
cover bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and sugar well; add eggs one at
a time.
Add	chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Bake at 450° for
10 minutes,
then
bake
at
for 35 minutes; chill overnight. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Chop bell pepper and onion.
Bone and dice chicken.
Combine 1 cup mushroom soup, 1 cup tomato soup, 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese and broth from chicken.
Add 1/2 can ripe olives.
Boil spaghetti until done and pour mixture over it.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick is inserted and comes clean.

title: gumbo
directions: Brown flour in oil, stirring constantly.
Add 1/2 chopped seasoning to brown flour and saute for about 1 minute.
Add this mixture to the 3 quarts boiling water; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining seasoning and bouillon cubes; boil for about 10 minutes. Add oysters (or other seafood) and simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to rapid boil; add file.
Mix well; remove from heat.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: rice and beans
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Add other ingredients and simmer many hours.
Serve over rice.
(Cannot be made in a crock-pot; needs to be made on a stove in a pot.)

title: midwestern chowder
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion, celery and thyme until soft. Add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper.
Cover with chicken broth and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add green pepper and corn; set aside.

title: christmas nut brittle
directions: Combine egg white and water.
Beat until very stiff.
Add nuts and coat well.
Stir combined sugar and cinnamon into nut mixture. Arrange in 1 layer on well greased brown paper (grocery sack) cut to fit cookie sheet.
Break up while still warm (not hot) at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into jello in large bowl until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Stir in ice cream until smooth. Pour into serving dish.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm. Garnish with Cool Whip, fruit and nuts.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat egg yolks until frothy. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick and lemon colored. Add whipping cream, vanilla, flour and cream of tartar to egg yolk mixture. Combine egg whites and salt; beat until stiff peaks form. Fold egg white mixture into egg yolks mixture; pour into 1-gallon freezer. Add enough milk to fill can.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the above except chili powder, paprika and chopped pecans.
Shape into a ball or mold of your choice.
Roll in chili powder, paprika and pecans.
This is good with crackers.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Combine and mix all the ingredients, except half the sugar and half the cinnamon.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon in another bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour half the batter into three lightly greased 6 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Repeat with remaining batter and cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Swirl lightly with a knife.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: master mix bread dough
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
In small bowl, combine water, margarine, sugar and salt.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Beat with wooden spoon.
With hands, work another 1/2 cup flour.
Remaining 1/2 cup of flour may be used as knead.
Knead about 12 minutes.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Knead again 45 seconds.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix everything together except for the butter and Ritz crackers and place in a casserole dish.
Then slice the butter and place on top of mixture; sprinkle crumbled Ritz crackers on top of butter pats.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and 2 teaspoons oil.
Stir in flour, then mix in corn.
Spoon by the spoonfuls into fat heated to 350° until golden brown.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: To the pineapple, add lemon juice, sugar and salt; mix.
Whip the cream and fold into the mixture. Fold in chilled rice and coconut. Chill. Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil, drain and mash squash and onion.
Season with butter, pepper and salt.
Add can of cream of chicken soup and container of sour cream.
In separate bowl, mix together stuffing mix and stick of melted butter.
In large casserole (3-quart) layer dressing, squash and dressing.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: polish cabbage soup or stew
directions: In 6 cups of water, simmer for 1 hour the next 6 ingredients. Add cabbage, ketchup, vinegar and sour cream; simmer 1 hour more. Add more water if needed.
Serve topped with sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Store in an airtight container.

title: marian's hot dish
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in a baking pan in the order listed.
Pour tomatoes on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
After an hour of baking, take out and spread the layer of cheese over.
Bake the last 30 minutes uncovered.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar. Mix well. Stir in egg and vanilla. Mix well.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Brown sirloin and mix with all other ingredients in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: mayme's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and simmer 15 minutes.
Makes about 1 quart of very good sauce for ribs or chicken.

title: butterhorns
directions: In a large bowl, cut butter into flour with a pastry blender or fork. Add egg yolk and sour cream. Mix well. Shape into a ball. Sprinkle with flour and wrap in waxed paper. Chill in refrigerator for several hours.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat a large

Dutch oven with a tight-fitting lid over medium-high heat. Pour in enough oil to fill the pan, about 1/4-inch deep. Season the beef generously with salt and pepper, and add to the pan. Saute the meat, uncovered, stirring only occasionally, until well-browned, about 8 minutes. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the beef to a plate. Repeat with the remaining beef. Discard the oil and wipe out the pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well; add bananas last.
Also nuts if desired.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: cranberry holiday salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add orange rind and cranberry sauce.
Chill until thickened.
Stir in pineapple and celery.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased mold.
Chill until firm. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour the rest of the ingredients in dish and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Top will get very brown.
During the last 5 minutes, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: saucy chicken manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine water and onions for 5 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Add onions, mushrooms, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add cooked chicken. Stuff shells.
Prepare cheese sauce mix according to package and pour over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May serve with extra cheese sauce.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper; add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through; stir often. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: avocado deviled eggs
directions: Set aside egg white; sieve yolks.
Combine yolks with remaining ingredients except avocado.
Mix well.
Fold in avocado; refill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with additional paprika.
If desired, top each with a pimento strip or a parsley sprig.
Chill. Makes 12.

title: johnnycake
directions: Sift the cornmeal and salt together.
Add the boiling water gradually while stirring into a thick batter.
Drop spoonfuls into a hot skillet with a thick film of fat on its bottom.
Turn when the bottom is browned; cooking time should be 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Drain on papers before serving.
Some cooks form the batter into oval pones instead of dropping spoon-scoops into the skillet.

title: crepe suzettes
directions: Combine sifted flour, sugar and salt in a mixing bowl. Add the whole eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add enough milk to make a thin batter. Beat until smooth. Stir in melted butter.
Pour about 1/2 cup batter into a heated lightly greased skillet. When brown on underside, turn and brown on the other side.
