Spread with marmalades, jams or jellies and roll.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix 1 cup bran with boiling water.
Stir and let set.
Cream together sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix together with remaining 2 cups bran and buttermilk and water and bran mixture.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.
Cook in muffin pans.
Keeps up to 6 weeks.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Boil ingredients together to hard crack stage.
Turn into greased pans.
Mark candy into squares when partly cold.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and cut potatoes as for thick French fries.
Place in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover potatoes with sugar and salt. Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over the sugar.
More can be used if desired.
Cover with pieces of butter.
Twist slices of lemon over this and place peel in with potatoes.
Sift flour evenly over potatoes.
Add water to mixture so it may be barely seen.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done and sugar and butter have made a thick syrup.
Baste potatoes frequently with syrup. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt peanut butter with butterscotch chips and chocolate chips with peanut butter in heavy saucepan, stirring constantly.
Fold in peanuts until well coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined tray.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Mix well.
Form into 4 patties and grill or broil.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken, pimento, green pepper and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup and broth over that.
Add salt, pepper and 1 1/4 cups cheese.
Add spaghetti; toss lightly.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Chill 1 hour before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Saute bacon; drain.
Place beef, butter and mushrooms in skillet; saute slightly.
Sprinkle with flour and pepper.
Add the milk; cook until thick.
Beat together until creamy the eggs, evaporated milk, salt and melted butter.
Alternate layers of eggs and sauce.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Simmer raisins in water for 2 minutes. Cool. Blend sugar, egg, molasses and shortening. Add raisin mixture. Stir in flour, salt and soda.

title: rotel
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Pressure for 8 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
In separate bowl, combine cocoa and melted butter; add to sugar mixture.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Chill for 3 hours.
Form 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly, then remove from pan.

title: cornish hens in rice stuffing
directions: Season hens with salt and pepper.
In saucepan, cook almonds, onion and rice in butter for 5 or 10 minutes.
Add water, bouillon cube, lemon juice and salt.
Boil slowly 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is fluffy.
Stir in mushrooms.
Brush hens with butter after stuffing with rice.
Roast in shallow covered pan at 400° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and roast 1 hour longer.
Brush birds with melted butter the last 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt 3/4 stick margarine in large bowl and 1/4 stick margarine in small pan.
Add cubed bread to large bowl and stir.
Mix in eggs, soup and chicken (cut up).
Stir all together and pour into greased casserole.
Crush crackers into crumbs and stir into butter in small pan.
Sprinkle cracker mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for one hour, uncovered.

title: greek korupiethes or crescent cookies
directions: To have the best taste, do not substitute margarine for the butter.
Cream the butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, and blend well after each addition.
Add the nuts.
Batter is now in a consistency to mold cookies by hand.
Shape in half moon about 1 1/2 inches long. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
They will not brown on top, only on bottom.
Take out of oven and place on wax paper which has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Sift more powdered sugar on top.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse well.
Chill overnight.
Add peas, onions, eggs, celery and mayonnaise to macaroni.
Season to taste.
Garnish with sliced egg.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in melted and cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg addition (medium speed).
Pour into crust and chill at least 2 hours.

title: chess pie
directions: In a saucepan, warm butter until melted on low heat.
Remove pan from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into two 9-inch prepared pie shells.
Cook 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce temperature to 325° and finish baking for 1 hour.
Pie will be done when custard is set.
Check with knife by inserting into center of pie and point comes out clean.

title: easy bake cheesecake
directions: Combine sugar, softened cream cheese, lemon juice, salt and vanilla in a mixing bowl. Begin to blend ingredients together. Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time. Pour mixture into unbaked Bama 9-inch graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Chill before serving. Garnish with your favorite fruit topping.

title: taco pie
directions: Place rolls in bottom of pie pan so they are covering entire bottom.
Bake rolls for about 12 to 15 minutes until golden.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Cream the cheese until soft, then mix in cool whip and cream of coconut. Chill for 2 hours. Serve with fresh fruits of your choice.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Beat well. Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into
a tube pan which has been well-greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Pour Sauce over top.

title: no fail turtles
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar and syrup.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk; save 1/2 can of milk. Mix with flour and then add to the mixture.
Stir constantly; this will burn very easy.
Boil to 240° on medium heat.
Pour over pecans.
This will fill a cookie sheet.
You may break and eat or top with melted chocolate flavor almond bark for a traditional turtle candy.

title: raisin cake
directions: Coat 2 boxes raisins (1 pound size) with 1/2 cup flour.
Cream well margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add flour, baking powder and lemon flavor.
Bake at 250° for approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Test cake with cake tester or straw.
Do not overcook.

title: special bread pudding
directions: Spread butter on crustless bread and cut each slice into fourths.
Arrange half of bread in bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with raisins and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cover with the rest of the bread and cinnamon.
Heat milk just until film forms over top.
Add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Gradually add hot milk mixture to beaten eggs beating constantly.
Stir in vanilla and pour over bread.
Set casserole in pan containing 1-inch hot water and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.
Serve warm or chilled with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all; put in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: sweet rolls
directions: In a pan combine milk, butter and salt and scald.
Let it cool completely.
In a bowl, combine water, sugar and yeast.
Stir and cool.
Mix these mixtures together when they are both cool.
Add about 4 cups of the flour and stir
until sticky.
Add the rest of the flour to knead.
On floured surface, knead for 10 minutes. Put in a greased bowl and let rise until it doubles.
Punch down. Cut into roll size sections.
Put in greased pans; let rise again. Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: best ever meatballs
directions: Combine and shape into balls.
Brown in oven or skillet. Transfer to slow cooker.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm stuffing
tossed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion cheese strata
directions: Separate onion slices into rings.
Cut off crusts of bread. In 9-inch pan, layer bread, onions and cheese (two layers).
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over layered ingredients; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° until firm. Drizzle melted butter over top before baking.
Serve warm or cool.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add egg and beat well.

Sift remaining dry ingredients and add to first mixture. This dough may be divided, adding melted chocolate and vanilla to one portion, grated coconut to another portion, nuts and raisins or chopped dates to another portion.
These portions may be made into sausage-like rolls, wrapped in waxed paper and placed in refrigerator overnight or until wanted.
Before baking, slice very thin.
Bake in hot oven on cookie sheet.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters and reserve liquor.
Dice oysters into a saucepan.
Add liquor and slowly bring to a boil.
Immediately remove pan from heat.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs.
Alternately add the 3 cups flour and buttermilk with soda dissolved in it.
Mix chopped fruit, nuts and candy orange slices with 1/2 cup flour.
Then add to batter mixture.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate yogurt cream pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and gelatin. Gradually stir in milk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and gelatin is dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add yogurt and vanilla; blend gently until well combined.
Pour into dessert dishes. Refrigerate 6 hours or until set.
Top with fruit.

title: pie apple sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat oil, molasses and egg together well.
Add yogurt and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add all at once to wet ingredients. Mix lightly; extra beating will toughen the cake.
Turn batter into a nonstick 9-inch square pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until center of cake springs back when touched lightly with fingertip. Cool briefly in pan on rack.
Serve warm with Lemon Syrup.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Place shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs in large mixing bowl; mix thoroughly.
Add oatmeal, dry ingredients, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 7 dozen.

title: hamburger hoagie
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and spices.
Cover and cook slowly on low heat approximately 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Make sure meat is well cooked.
Drain.
Line hoagie roll with cheese slices, spoon in meat.

title: azra's khir(indian rice pudding)
directions: In saucepan, 5 to 6-quart, bring milk to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly to prevent skin from forming.
Reduce heat and stir.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add rice and keep stirring for 30 minutes, or until rice is very soft and milk has disintegrated. Add the sugar and chopped almonds and stir for 15 minutes over low heat.

title: diet applesauce mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of hot water.
Add 2 cups cold water. Put 1/2 cup applesauce in 8 individual cups.
Pour 1/2 cup jello over applesauce in cups and mix well.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.
One serving = 1 fruit.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients, drop by spoonful (depending on size you want) into hot oil.
Makes 12 large hush puppies.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook beef. Drain. Add taco mix. Spread refried beans in bottom of 9 x 13 casserole dish. Spread sour cream on top of refried beans. Sprinkle beef on top of sour cream. Add cheese on top of beef. Slice in slices to cover the beef. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: milky way cake
directions: Prepare cake following directions on box.
Melt 12 ounces of candy bars with stick of margarine or butter or the oil.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into cake pan and bake.

title: angel food cake
directions: Have eggs at room temperature before using.
Start oven at 375°.
Sift flour and sugar once before measuring.

title: lemon pie bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie dough. Pat into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Mix next 4 ingredients. Pour over baked crust. Bake 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cinnamon, until blended.
Pour into oblong baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Shake the biscuit pieces in a plastic bag, to coat with the cinnamon and white sugar.
Pour into a greased bundt or angel food pan.
Layer and sprinkle with nuts.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add baking soda to sour cream. Alternate adding sour cream (mixed with baking soda) and flour to sugar.
Pour batter into pie dish.
Sprinkle on top with brown sugar, ground sugar, cinnamon and small bits of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: baked apricot halves
directions: Place apricot halves in baking dish.
Crumble crackers over apricots.
Sprinkle brown sugar and margarine pieces over mixture. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood bake
directions: Mix all together, except cheese, last half of chopped pecans and cracker crumbs.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and pecans that have been mixed together.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chocoroon pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Combine milk and coconut and spoon over chocolate mixture, leaving 1/2 to 1 inch border.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In heavy pot, melt butter.
Add oil and saute all seasonings until done. Add flour and blend well. Add tomato sauce, hot water and sugar. Cook over medium heat approximately 30 minutes. Add shrimp and cook another 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cake muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 18 muffin pan with paper liners or grease them well.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix together butter, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla about 4 minutes.
Add flour mixture, alternating with milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Scoop about 1/4 cup batter into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: ruby red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add raspberries and stir until berries are thawed and separated.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; chill until set.
Spread sour cream over mixture.
Chill.
Dissolve cherry gleatin in remaining water. Add pineapple and cranberry sauce; mix well.
Allow to thicken slightly.
Carefully spoon over sour cream mixture.
Chill.
Cut into squares and place over lettuce leaves.
Top with a dollop of mayonnaise.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir into stuffing, then add egg and sausage.
Blend thoroughly. Chill for about an hour for easier handling.
Then shape into small oblongs, about the size of pecans.
Cut bacon strips into thirds, crosswise; wrap one piece around dressing mixture and fasten with wooden pick.
Place on rack in shallow pan and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown and crisp, turning at halfway point in cooking.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.
May be made the day before baking; also freezes well before baking.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and drain.
In a 2 1/2-quart baking dish, add melted butter, onion and green onions.
Cook in microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes.
Add cauliflower to mixture and mix well.
Add bread crumbs and mix.
Add cheese and mix well.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is well melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and squash in a little oil until onion is translucent. Cover and let steam for a few minutes. Mix squash, onion, carrots and sour cream. Melt butter and toss with stuffing. Place the stuffing in a casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Drain apricots (save 1/2 cup juice). Place apricots, cherries and pineapple chunks in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cut pineapple slices in half and lay on top.
Combine butter, brown sugar, curry and apricot juice and pour over fruit.
Bake about 15 minutes, until thoroughly heated. Serve warm topped with sour cream and coconut.

title: rice and beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: hot rolls
directions: Bring milk to boil in saucepan.
Let rise to the top of pot. In the meantime, put yeast in rather warm water to dissolve.
After milk boils, put in large bowl along with yeast mixture.
Add butter with salt and sugar.
Let sit until mixture is cool.
Add enough flour until the mixture is just right to knead on floured counter.
If sticky, add more flour.
Put in large greased bowl. Take out and knead again.
Put in bowl again.
Let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Take dough out and cut until you have medium sized rolls.
Put on cookie sheet.
It may be covered with aluminum foil.
Let rise for about 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° or 375° until golden brown.
Take out and grease top with a little cooking oil.
Cinnamon and sugar may be sprinkled on rolls after you cut them to rise on cookie sheet.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Spray 2 pizza sheets with Pam. Spread the dough on sheets. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes only! Let cool completely. Spread Cool Whip on crusts and top with fruits as you wish.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening in a large bowl.
Add sugars gradually, beating until well blended.
Beat in egg, vanilla and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoons onto well-greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until golden, about 15 minutes. Yields 5 dozen.

title: candied apples
directions: Wash, quarter and core apples.
(Rome Beauties work best.) Place apples in a saucepan with sugar and water.
Cook slowly, uncovered, and stir frequently for about 1 hour or until apples are transparent.

title: pickled watermelon rind
directions: Cut rind into 1-inch cubes; trim off outer green skin and bright pink flesh.
Soak overnight in enough salted water to cover; drain.
Heat sugar and vinegar to boiling.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Add spice bag and melon rind to vinegar mixture. Cook, uncovered, until melon is transparent, about 45 minutes. Discard spice bag.
If desired, add a few drops red or green food coloring to the rind.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Spoon chicken and cheese into each crescent roll to enclose filling.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Prepare soup using package directions.
Pour over rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Use half of butter, half of cream cheese and half of the powdered sugar.
Mix together.
In another bowl, mix 1/2 milk, 1 package pudding and 1/2 of whipped cream.
Combine both mixtures. Repeat with the second pudding.
Cover any holes in bottom of flower pot with foil.
Layer 1/3 cookies, vanilla pudding, 1/3 cookies, chocolate pudding and top with remaining cookies. Refrigerate overnight.
Add flower or shovel.
Put gummy worms between layers.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Spread in large casserole dish (9 x 12-inch).
Combine Dream Whip and milk.
Whip until thick.
Add powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Whip together until smooth.
Pour over cracker crust.
Pour canned filling over top.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix with mixer and put in salad dish.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Mash in blender until smooth, no lumps.
Place all ingredients in bowl, mix one at a time.
Use hand mixer and add milk last.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil on high heat for 1 hour. Then turn on low and simmer for 4 to 8 hours.

title: chicken and chinese vegetables
directions: In small bowl, combine chicken broth, cornstarch, sherry and soy sauce; blend well.
Set aside.
Heat large skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add oil; heat until it ripples.
Add chicken; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.

title: frozen tomato aspic
directions: Combine all ingredients except the gelatin and mayonnaise and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Strain.
Add the gelatin and dissolve in the hot mixture.
Allow to cool.
Fold in the mayonnaise; pour into individual molds and freeze.
Unmold and garnish with avocado slices, if desired.

title: salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Add bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Pour half in container and let congeal, then spread sour cream on top.
Add the remaining Jell-O mixture.

title: festive baked ham
directions: Combine apple cider and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Set aside.
Remove skin from ham.
Place ham, fat side up, on a cutting board.
Score fat in a diamond design and stud with cloves.
Place ham in a shallow baking pan, fat side up; coat top with brown sugar.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat or bone.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 22 to 25 minutes per pound, about 2 hours, basting every 20 to 30 minutes with cider mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Serve sauce with sliced ham.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage into large bowl.
Place onion and pepper on top. Sprinkle with sugar.
Heat vinegar, oil, celery seed, mustard and salt (to just a boil); remove from heat and pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir, then drain before serving.
(Will keep in refrigerator for several days.)

title: oyster casserole
directions: Put 1/2 oysters in bottom of casserole.
Combine crackers, salt, pepper and butter; toss to mix.
Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over oysters, then another layer of oysters.
Add Worcestershire to milk and pour over oysters.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
If more moist oysters are desired, use 2 cups milk.

title: salsa
directions: Put tomatoes, mangos, peppers and onions through food processor, then mix in sugar, salt and vinegar.
Adjust peppers to suit your taste.

title: calabacitas con carne
directions: Brown steak in shortening.
Reduce heat, add water, cover and simmer until tender, about one hour.
Add more water as needed. Saute squash and onion in shortening until tender.
Add corn, green chile and seasonings.
Add meat and meat stock to vegetables. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add grated cheese.
Stir to melt.
Yields 8 servings.

title: salmon pie
directions: Crust:
Combine flour, salt and paprika; cut in butter and 1 cup of cheese.
Stir in nuts.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press in bottom of a 10-inch pie plate.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter, flour and nuts together well; keep aside 1/2 cup for top.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup of crumbs over the top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg to pumpkin.
Add eggs, Milnot and hot water.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° until done.
(I double this for 16-ounce can of pumpkin.
Makes three 8-inch pies.)

title: fruit cake
directions: Bake cookie dough according to directions on tube. Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over baked crust.
Top with favorite fruit (fresh or canned).

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: asparagus-tomato stir-fry
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring until blended.
Set aside.

title: cheese soup #2
directions: Saute onions and carrots in 1/2 stick oleo.
Add the chicken broth and bring to a boil. Simmer 30 minutes. Add the potato soup, sour cream and cheese.
Let simmer to melt the cheese.
Keep hot.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Drain shrimp.
Put in bowl and mince well with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Shake some paprika on top.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours to chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: microwave toffee
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in 9-inch square pan; set aside.
Coat the top 2 inches of a 2 1/2 quart glass bowl with butter; place remaining butter in bowl.
Add sugar, salt and water; do not stir. Microwave at High for 11 minutes or until mixture just begins to turn light brown.
Pour over pecans.
Sprinkle with morsels; let stand 1 minute.
Spread morsels over sugar mixture and sprinkle with 1/4 cup finely chopped pecans.
Chill until firm.
Break into bite size pieces.
Yields 1 pound.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and water, making a smooth paste.
Add egg yolks and milk which have been well mixed.
Place over low fire, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into large Pyrex dish which has been buttered and layered with bananas and wafers.
Beat egg whites.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Pour on top of pudding; golden brown.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Drain well.
Into a 1 3/4-quart casserole dish, mix beef mixture, soup, Chinese vegetables, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle Chinese noodles on top of casserole.
Cook for 10 more minutes or until noodles are browned.
Serve as is or over cooked rice.

title: breakfast
directions: In a skillet heat oil, add French fries and cook until done. Cover while cooking.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add onion, pepper and cheese. Add ham to French fries in skillet.
When fries are done, stir around for about 1 minute.
Spread out fries and ham around in skillet.
Now pour in egg mixture.
Cook about 2 to 3 minutes. Fold over with spatula to other side.
Cook a little.
Turn off heat.
Cook this over medium heat.
Don't burn your eggs.
Serve.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and pineapple. Boil for 10 minutes or a little longer if needed.
Stir in jello.
Pour in hot jars and seal (boil seals before using).

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Sift dry ingredients and add cooled butter.
Add brown sugar, then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.

title: taco sauce
directions: Chop peppers, onions and garlic in blender or food processor. Break bay leaves and add to all ingredients in a large pan, including tomatoes.
Cook on medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring frequently.
Prepare jars for canning.
Ladle cooked sauce into jars; put lids on and boil in hot bath of canner for 30 minutes.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Separate wings at joints and remove tips.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate, turning chicken occasionally, at least 1 hour.

title: zucchini fruit bread
directions: Lightly mix sugar, zucchini and oil.
Add eggs; mix well. Combine flour, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and baking powder. Gradually add to egg mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in pecans, raisins and pineapple.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased and floured loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Heat the first 5 ingredients; cool mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients to the cooled mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll; cut with cookie cutters.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Frost when cool.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, water and nuts in heavy saucepan over high heat.
Stir with wooden spoon until shade darker than light brown sugar.
Pour into buttered tinfoil, approximately 10 x 13-inches.
While hot, drop candy bars on top and spread with knife.
Sprinkle ground nuts on top.
Cool in refrigerator.
Break into pieces and refrigerate.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine all wet ingredients; mix well.
Gradually add dry ingredients to wet mixture.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl place cabbage, onion and green pepper.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Bring to boiling point.
Immediately pour over vegetables.
Add salt, black pepper and celery seed.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours or longer.
Yields 4 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Sift remaining dry ingredients.
Sift 1/2 dry ingredients into sugar/oil mixture.
Alternate remaining dry ingredients with eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and nuts; mix well.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in slow oven (325°) about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cake cool slightly before removing from pan. When cool, frost with cream cheese or Caramel Frosting.

title: peacheesy pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut shortening into flour and salt until size of peas.
Sprinkle peach syrup over mixture, stirring until dough holds together.
Roll out half of dough on floured surface to 1/6-inch thickness.
Fit into 9-inch pie pan.
Fill with Peach Mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cover with Cheesecake Topping.
Roll out remaining dough; cut into circles.
Brush with peach syrup.
Arrange on topping.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Cover edge with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until deep golden brown.

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: Combine cocoa and boiling water, stirring until smooth; set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt in medium bowl; add to creamed mixture alternately with cocoa mixture, beating with electric mixer at low speed, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Do not overbeat. Pour batter into greased and floured pans (use three 9-inch round pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes; test center of cake with toothpick.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks before frosting.

title: spanish hot dog sauce
directions: Heat together tomato sauce and tomato juice; add the spices to taste.
Brown hamburger and large chopped onion.
Mix and heat all together.

title: crab dip
directions: Cream cheese, Miracle Whip and lemon juice and add other ingredients.
Combine and chill.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and vanilla extract.
Stir with a spoon until well blended and smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups Nestle semi-sweet morsels and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread with rest of nuts and morsels.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: 8-inch pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into pastry-lined pan.
Cook at 375° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: congealed green salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until partially congealed.
Combine avocado, lemon juice, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Mix peas, chopped ingredients, pepper sauce and salt.
Add avocado mixture.
Combine with gelatin.
Pour into a lightly oiled 4 to 5 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: molasses coconut chews
directions: Combine syrup, molasses, vinegar and butter.
Place over low flame and stir until mixture boils.
Continue boiling to 240° or until small amount of syrup becomes brittle in cold water.
Remove from fire; add coconut.
Drop from 2 forks on greased surface. Makes 28 chews.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; put in casserole.
Cut up chestnuts in mix with beans and soup; cover all with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole. Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and green onions; saute until softened, about 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and continue to saute 5 minutes.
Stir in half of artichokes and the spinach.
Cook until warm, about 3 minutes.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with a fork.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in large bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over top of vegetables.
Crumble bacon over mayonnaise.
Spread cheese over bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: musterole
directions: Saute meat, oleo and onions.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Boil 1 package macaroni (shells) in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Add meat mixture.
Then add soup mixture.
Last, add 1 pound Velveeta cheese and cook only until cheese melts.
This is a skillet dish and very good.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, onion, garlic and celery.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, worcestershire sauce, green onions, salt, accent and 1/2 of the dried beef.
Shape into a ball and put remaining dried beef on outside of the ball.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, peanut butter, graham crumbs and butter; mix until well blended.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: corn sticks or muffins
directions: Bake in well-greased muffin or corn pone pan at 450° until done.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, celery, carrots, onion and all seasoning. Cook until tender. Add potatoes; cook until they are tender. Add milk to flour, then add to vegetables and cook until thick. Add cheese; stir until cheese melts. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Put eggplant into cold, salted water (whole).
Boil until it can be pierced with a fork.
Peel, mash and season with salt, pepper and butter.
Add egg and flour.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot, greased griddle.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over ice.

title: rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup water, 1/2 cup sugar and shortening.
Heat to melt shortening; cool.
Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in 1/4 cup water.
Add to shortening mixture.
Add eggs, flour and salt.
Let raise for 1 hour.
Stir down and refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Heat together soup, sugar, salt, mustard, oil, vinegar and Worcestershire.
Mix well.
Pour over carrots, onions and pepper. Marinate overnight.
Heat before serving.

title: hot breakfast cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with dry pudding and nuts.
Melt the oleo.
Add sugar and spice and drizzle over the rolls.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Let stand overnight.
Remove foil.
Bake next morning at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife around pan before inverting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs or crushed potato chips. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: communion bread (crackers)
directions: Sift or mix dry ingredients.
Work in butter to fine meal. Add milk and stir well.
Refrigerate mixture about 1/2 hour.
Roll out very thin and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cut to desired size.
Bake at 325° to 350° until light brown.
Watch closely. Enjoy!

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and spread half of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on; cool, peel and grate into large bowl.
Mix the rest of the ingredients, except for the bread crumbs.
Put potatoes and mixture into well-buttered casserole. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix and stir until red hots are dissolved.
